title: sweet potato pie
directions: Sieve sweet potatoes which are boiled.
Add ingredients in the order mentioned.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 400° for 10 minutes and lower to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
For a richer pie, add 2/3 cup evaporated milk and 1/3 cup water.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: About 20 minutes before serving pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of the juice, set pineapple chunks and juice aside.
Mix flour and salt.
Coat chicken.
Cook chicken in skillet in oil until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes on each side.
Remove and put into baking dish.
In the drippings, stir honey, teriyaki sauce, chives and pineapple juice.
Boil 30 seconds.
Add pineapple chunks. Heat thoroughly.
Pour over chicken.
Serve.

title: fried dumplings
directions: Soak flowers in salt water solution for 15 minutes.
Shake off and dip in flour batter.
Fry in hot oil until batter is crisp. Remove from oil and place on a paper towel covered dish.
Lightly salt.
Serve hot.
Tastes like fried zucchini.

title: chocolate chips cookies
directions: I make 'em with my daddy.
We put flour in a bowl, chocolate chips.
You get a beater.
You stir it with a spoon and then put 'em in the microwave, you eat 'em.
All of us after supper.
I eat a lot!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth until almost done (don't overcook). In a large saucepan, melt the cheese in the milk, stirring constantly, over low heat. Stir in the noodles (with the chicken broth) and the chicken.
It should be quite juicy. Pour into large casserole or make two smaller ones. Can be frozen at this point.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour and brown sugar thoroughly.
Melt oleo and mix with flour mixture.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together and spread over cookie mixture.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Sift flour with spice. Cream butter until soft and smooth. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, lemon juice and vanilla extract, beating thoroughly. Add flour-spice mixture gradually. Chop all fruit and nuts. Roll or toss in part of the flour to coat them. Gradually add to cake batter. Turn into well-greased loaf pans or molds that have been lined with greased brown paper (may use buttered waxed paper or buttered parchment baking paper). Bake in slow oven (250°) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water.
Cool.
Add pineapple.
Grind orange and cranberries in food processor.
Add to gelatin.
Finely chop celery, apple and nuts.
Add to gelatin mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick sweet pickles
directions: Drain and rinse pickles.
Mix other ingredients together. Pour over drained pickles.
Put back in jars.
Store in refrigerator.
Resist eating for 5 days.
M-M-Good!

title: pot roast of beef
directions: Place vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Salt and pepper. Brush with Kitchen Bouquet, if desired.
Add water; cover and cook 10 to 12 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Grate carrots and radishes.
Mix
sour cream, mayonnaise, dill weed and soup mix.
Use fat-free sour cream and low-fat mayonnaise for a low-fat dip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Mix onions, soup, eggs and mayonnaise.
Mix in broccoli.
Put in a 10-inch baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter and spread over top.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until a knife is inserted and comes out clean.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: zippy cheddar crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 2 large baking sheets; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine cornmeal, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir in boiling water, mixing until blended.
Stir in cheese, onions, peppers and pimiento.
Drop level teaspoon batter, 1 inch apart onto prepared baking sheets.
With spatula flatten batter into 2-inch rounds.
Bake 18 minutes or until golden and slightly brown around edges.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine all and mix 2 minutes on high with mixer. Pour into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.	Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.	Add flavoring. Mix. Pour
mixture into greased and floured tube pan; bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with Brown Sugar Frosting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until it thickens.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells or 1 deep-dish shell.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: ice cream
directions: In a big pan, scald milk.
Mix yolks and sugar.
Add some scalded milk in sugar and egg mixture.
Then put in big pan and add light syrup.
Cook until mixture coats spoon.
When mixture cools, add vanilla and egg whites.
Put mixture in ice cream can and add milk to fill can.
Chill and freeze.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Make 2 hours before serving:
Just before serving add:

title: austin carter's favorite dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (8-ounce) cups.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix together first six ingredients, then add Cool Whip and chill.

title: polish sausage casserole
directions: Cook up spaghetti noodles; drain.
Add butter, salt and Parmesan cheese to taste.
Boil Polish sausage, slice up, add to noodles and sprinkle parsley flakes on.
Fast, easy and delicious!

title: one step yogurt pound cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend at low speed.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour batter in greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until top springs back.
You may frost or serve plain.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease in frying pan.
Let them fry until golden brown.

title: stew-fried shrimp
directions: In large iron skillet or Dutch oven, fry salt pork until golden brown; set salt pork slices aside.
Slice onion in pork fat and cook until brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken breasts, seasoned with salt and garlic, in water until tender.
Cook egg noodles per package directions.
Chop celery and onions.
Cover with chicken broth and cook until tender (discard rest of chicken broth).
Heat the soups and Velveeta cheese together until the cheese is melted.
(Do not add water to the soups; use soups direct from the cans.)
Add onions and celery to mixture.
Stir in noodles and diced chicken.
Add peas.

title: peppered shrimp(very hot and spicy!)
directions: In heavy, 10-quart Dutch oven, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until butter or margarine is a rich hazelnut brown, about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp to sauce; stir gently to coat well.
Cook over medium heat just until all shrimp are coral pink, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tasty soup
directions: *Or use 1 1/2 cups frozen veggies.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding, fruit cocktail and sour cream until creamy. Serve cold.

title: fricidillis
directions: Mix
all ingredients well.
Mixture will be soft.
Drop by big spoonfuls	into
hot
skillet.
Brown
on	both sides. Place in a
baking
dish.
Blend
soup and one can water with drippings from meat.	Mix and pour over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: grilled fish
directions: Salt and pepper fish and place in tinfoil (individual foil containers per fish steak).
Leave extra foil on sides of foil containers so you can make a tent.
Pour Italian dressing over fish until covered.
Place on grill over medium hot coals and close foil tents for a few minutes.
Then open and cook until fish is nice and white all the way through.

title: country breakfast fixings
directions: Cover bottom of skillet with bacon slices.
Place ham on top of bacon.
Cook slowly either on top of stove or in oven.
Turn bacon once; also turn ham slices, keeping ham on top of bacon. Bacon will have a country ham flavor (heavenly).
Serve with eggs, grits and biscuits for a perfect breakfast.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add milk to pudding and beat exactly 2 minutes.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer wafers and bananas; pour pudding to cover.
Put another layer of wafers and bananas.
Pour remaining pudding mixture over this.
Garnish with finely crushed wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: In large bowl, combine.
Put frozen strawberries in jello and hot water.
Mix well, then set up for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then pour over second layer of salad.
Refrigerate and let set up good.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir every 5 minutes for 20 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
You may double recipe.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling salted water for 2 minutes. Drain.
Mix meats, crushed crackers, onion, salt and pepper.
Add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Place 3 tablespoons of meat mixture on each leaf and roll.
Fasten with toothpick.
Put in large skillet and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover skillet and simmer about 1 hour.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown the seasoned chicken in the vegetable oil.
Remove and brown sausage in same skillet.
Remove the sausage and most of the oil from the skillet.
Add the onions, garlic, bell pepper and green onions.
Brown the vegetables, adding water to keep them from sticking to the skillet.
In a 16 to 20-quart pot, place the browned vegetables.
Add the chicken and sausage.
Add the tomatoes and the 10 cups of water.
Add salt and peppers to taste.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil and add the washed rice.
When this comes to a good boil again, lower the heat and let the water boil out. Stir well and lower the fire again, then cover.
After 15 minutes, uncover, stir well and cover again.
Do not keep stirring.
Leave over a low flame for 45 minutes; excess stirring will make the rice mushy.
Makes 16 quarts.
May be frozen for 2 months.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and then add this mixture to sugar and cornstarch.
Add butter and pineapple; cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: Place potatoes and onions on double thickness of aluminum foil. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap tightly. Cook on grill over direct heat for about 1 hour or until tender, turning potatoes over half way through cooking.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Peel and clean carrots.
Cook until tender, drain and slice. Place in a bowl.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in pan and cook until heated, then pour over carrots.
Let set overnight.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick side dish stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter 8 minutes stirring.
Add broth and raisins, bring to a boil.
Occasionally stir in stuffing mix.
Cover & cook over low heat 2 minutes or heated through. Serve as a side dish with chicken, turkey or pork.
May be placed in a greased baking dish and refrigerated.
To serve, cover and bake at 350° 30 minutes or until hot.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine and seasonings.
Layer beans, carrots and mushrooms in casserole.
Top with onions.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream shortening; add sugars and beat well.
Add peanut butter, egg, water and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: kielbasa sausage
directions: Cook, covered, in a crock-pot on high for 3 hours.
Uncover and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: For fresh vegetables, cook until tender. For frozen vegetables, cook as directed. Drain and put in bottom of large baking pan. In saucepan, mix soup, onion, cheese and mayonnaise; heat. Add beaten eggs to saucepan; mix. Pour over vegetables. Cover with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred the cabbage. Shred the onions and separate the rings. In a large glass bowl, put a layer of cabbage, layer of onions and 1/4 cup sugar, then second layer of cabbage, second layer of onions and 1/4 cup sugar. Make third layer the same way. Now, in a pot, put the vinegar, oil, 1 tablespoon sugar, celery salt and prepared mustard. Bring to a boil. Pour all vinegar solution over cabbage. Cover. Toss after couple mix and let sit in the refrigerator until next day. (Has to always be made the day before.)

title: peanut butter rice krispies treat
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and butter to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix lightly.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press mixture into pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and package of Knorr vegetable soup, chopped green onions and chopped water chestnuts.
Add the chopped spinach that has been thawed, drained and squeezed dry.
Mix the ingredients well and then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add sugar, eggs, oil and strawberries.
Mix well.
Divide into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for a few minutes. This is excellent to serve with strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydew, bananas, kiwi and grapes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and pour into a dish and freeze.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 12 cake pan. Peel, core and chop apples. Beat eggs. Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts. Pour in cake pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool. Top with cream cheese icing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: ground beef vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Mix together soda and sour cream and set aside. Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and sour cream mixture alternately to butter mixture. Stir in bananas and chocolate chips. Add vanilla and salt. Place in a greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes. Use cake tester.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix together wafers and butter.
Press 3/4 of mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: fudge icing for brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Boil until blisters, then beat until thick.

title: barbecued shrimp and bacon
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Wrap each shrimp with a bacon slice. Thread each shrimp on a small bamboo skewer and brush lightly with oil before broiling.
Place skewers on a wire rack set into a foil-lined metal tray.
Broil the shrimp until the bacon gets crispy on all sides.
Baste with barbecue sauce and broil for 2 minutes.
Turn once and finish another 3 to 6 minutes or until shrimp are just cooked through.
Serve warm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and raisins in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in egg with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple mixture. Drizzle with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix cornbread mix with	eggs
and
milk.
Bake	at 425° until done.
Take cooked	cornbread and soften bread, mix well using the drippings.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Use 1 to 2
cans chicken
broth.
Bake
in
large pan until celery and onions are done.

title: marvelous muffins
directions: In a large bowl, grate the carrots, apples, pecans and dates. Add the coconut, eggs, oil and vanilla and mix in. Add dry ingredients gradually and mix gently after each addition. Spoon into sprayed muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: tex bake
directions: Brown cut up chicken with teaspoon oil in pan.
In another pan, brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning to each.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with Triscuits.
Add chicken, ground beef and cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add lettuce and optional ingredients.

title: swedish apple bread pudding
directions: Place bread slices in single layer in shallow pan.
Evenly drizzle 1/2 cup half and half over bread.
In medium saucepan, mix sugar and water; bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Return to medium heat.
Add 1/3 of apple slices and simmer each portion 3 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon.
Reserve sugar syrup.
Line a buttered shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish; top with 1/2 of poached apples. Make a layer of another 1/3 of the bread.
Cover evenly with remaining apples.
Cover with rest of bread.
Beat eggs; mix in cinnamon and cardamon, then 1 1/2 cups half and half and sugar syrup from poaching apples.
Pour egg mixture evenly over bread. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until top layer is brown and crusty (1 hour).

title: cucumber and yogurt spread(tzatziki)
directions: Line sieve with cheesecloth and put over bowl.
Dump yogurt into sieve and let strain in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, wash and grate cucumber coarsely.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Drain off juice.
Mix strained yogurt, garlic, vinegar, cucumber and olive oil.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: peach and grape flambe
directions: Step 1:
Caramelize sugar (heat sugar in pan until sugar turns brown; stir constantly).

title: john's famous brotherhood ham
directions: Use heavy gauge aluminum foil and a large skillet or baking pan.
Line pan with the foil, crisscross and have pieces of foil long enough to cover ham.
Place ham in pan on foil and score the top of ham in crisscross pattern with sharp knife.

Fold foil up around the ham, then slowly pour can of Coca-Cola over entire ham. Pat brown sugar on top of ham, then drizzle the honey on the ham. Seal ham securely with foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for crust and place in large glass pie dish.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Whip Dream Whip per instructions. Add confectioners sugar (one cup at a time) and blend well. Soften cream cheese and add to Dream Whip.
Whip and blend.
Pour into crust and refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and cover with 1 can of Thank You cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sugar-free fruit cocktail salad
directions: I keep a large can of fruit cocktail and a can of crushed or tidbits pineapple in the refrigerator at all times.
When needed, I open them and drain.
Add miniature marshmallows and coconut and then mix with Cool Whip or any whipped topping.

title: very low fat pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Chill or freeze and serve.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift first five ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until like cornmeal.
Beat egg.
Add orange juice and rind to egg then add to dry ingredients.
Carefully fold in fruits and nuts. Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Done when toothpick is clean when inserted.
Cool on wire rack.

title: chicken country captain
directions: Fry parsley, green peppers and onions in cooking oil slowly for 15 minutes.
Put this mixture in roaster.
Add tomatoes, spices, salt and pepper; simmer 15 minutes, then add garlic. Dredge chicken in a mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Fry until brown.
Lay chicken in the sauce; simmer at 275° in a covered roaster for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add currants 1/2 hour before serving.
Arrange rice on a large platter.
Pour sauce over this and place pieces of chicken on top.
Sprinkle toasted almonds on chicken.
Serves 8.

title: spiced apple pickles
directions: Peel, de-seed and slice cucumbers.
Soak 24 hours in lime and enough water to cover.
Rinse well.
Mix together 1 cup vinegar, alum and red food coloring.
Cover with water and simmer 2 hours. Drain.
Mix together 2 cups vinegar, 4 cups water, sugar, cinnamon candy and cinnamon sticks.
Bring this mixture to a boil every day for 3 days.
On the third day, pack in jars.
Makes about 7 quarts.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Blend bananas, oil, milk, nuts and egg.
Add flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour into paper lined muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a shallow baking dish and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix by hand in a large bowl.
Pour into 3-quart microwavable cake dish (Bundt style best).
Let set for 5 minutes.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes.
Let cool 4 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting or Cool Whip.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with peanuts.
Melt chips with milk.
Stir in marshmallows.
Melt.
Pour over peanuts.
Sprinkle remaining peanuts on top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: oatmeal flatbrod
directions: Sift flour; mix with oatmeal, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Divide dough in 10 parts.
Roll each part very thin (use a knobbed rolling pin if you have one).
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: tipsy prunes
directions: Place prunes in bottom of 2-quart glass jar and pour vodka over them.
Put jar in warm place and let sit for at least three weeks. Longer is better, if you can stand it.
The liquid makes a great prune liquor and three of the prunes for breakfast will keep Grandma in the pink all day long.
If Grannie is over 90, better use 100 proof vodka.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stuffing mix and margarine.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
Sprinkle stuffing mixture on top; place back in oven for a few minutes.

title: christmas sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the sour cream or buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; beat.
Sift together and add the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Roll out dough and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 10 minutes or less.

title: three hour rolls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together. Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add beaten egg and then fill the cup with milk. beat this into the flour mixture and let stand for 2 hours. Knead and roll out into rolls. Let rise for 1 hour. Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Prepare rice and seasoning according to package.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, pimiento, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in a large casserole dish.
Add cut-up chicken. Sprinkle rice on chicken.
Add soups and water.
Add chopped up onion.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Make crust first:
Mix macaroon crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar, softened butter and 1 tablespoon water.
Mix well; pat into an 8-inch cake pan and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Pour fruit and juice over marshmallows.
Whip cream and fold into marshmallow mixture.
Add strawberries and pecans.
Put into tray and freeze.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle pudding, sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter and pour over rolls.
Let rise all night.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties and fry in hot grease in skillet.
Makes great sandwiches.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and stuff mushroom caps.
Bake about 20 minutes at 275°.

title: peanut butter maple cookies
directions: Blend syrup into cookie mix.
Form into roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Dough may also be dropped by spoon.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers and butter.
Press in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Add whipped whipping cream.
Pour into cracker crust and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Add pie filling to top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar and butter; add egg, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour to mixture.
Make into ball.
Chill.
Roll and cut out with cutters. Bake at 350° until brown on cookie sheet.
Can be doubled.

title: pudding in a pot
directions: You will also need 1 six-inch clean clay pot, 1 silk flower with long stem, wax paper and ribbon.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Rinse pinto beans thoroughly.
Combine beans and cold water in a kettle or Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling.
Simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand one hour.
(Or add beans to cold water and soak overnight.)
Do not drain.
Add ham hocks and onion.
Cover; cook over low heat, for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove ham hocks.
Remove meat from bones; dice. Discard bones.
Return meat to beans.
Add tomato paste, chopped chili peppers and sugar.
Cover and cook until beans are tender, about 30 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Add additional water, if needed.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and taco mix.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
refried beans, sour cream mixture, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, green onions and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients
in
order listed in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Put beef in bottom of pan or glass cooking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and spoon on top of beef. Bake until brown.
You may layer the cornbread mix with the beef and cheese.

title: cadillos
directions: Dice pork and brown in oil.
Add chopped onion and saute a few minutes.
Add jalapeno chilies and stewed tomatoes.
Salt and cumin.
Let simmer until tender.
Add a bit of water if mixture gets too thick before it is tender.
Use to fill tacos, burritos or over rice.
Sprinkle cheese over.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; tear into bites.
Mix crackers with melted butter.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with crackers.
Place chicken pieces over crumbs.
Mix sour cream, soup and broth.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let sit for several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, cut the top off the bread and scoop out the insides.
Put the dip into the shell of the bread. Serve the scooped out insides and fresh cut vegetables with the dip.
Delicious!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Blend all this together until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening, ginger and cinnamon together and set aside 3/4 cup of dry mixture for topping.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the remainder.
Pour mixture into 8-inch square, greased baking dish and sprinkle the reserved dry mixture over the top to form an icing.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine in a bowl the cream cheese, Velveeta cheese, pimentos (drained) and 1 package dry dip mix. Mix together until well blended. Roll in pecans and chill in refrigerator overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: protein fruit cake
directions: The beans should be soaked overnight and then cooked in water to cover in the usual manner, adding no salt or meat.
Cook until tender enough to mash with a fork.
Cream melted margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat in mashed beans.
Sift dry ingredients together, then stir into bean mixture.
Stir in raisins, apples and nuts.

title: banana pudding(low in fats)
directions: Mix pudding as directions give.
Add pineapple without juice. Add sliced bananas.
Pour over crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: oreo pie
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble cookies on bottom of pan.
Melt cream cheese in microwave.
Mix with sugar.
Pour over cookies. Mix pudding by directions and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top of this. Crumble more cookies on top of pie. Chill for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan to 275° on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts, stirring until syrup turns light brown and peanuts begin to pop.
Remove from heat and add margarine, vanilla and soda.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan and spread to cover pan.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: chocolate creme pie
directions: Bake a single pie crust and cool.
Combine dry ingredients with
milk
and
cook
over
medium
heat until thick and bubbly. Lower
the heat and add the egg yolks.
Cook a little longer and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with a meringue and bake at 350° until meringue is slightly brown.

title: yeast rolls(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Heat water with butter added until butter melts. Mix flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Add water and egg. Knead on floured surface about 5 minutes. Put in greased bowl and let rise until double. Divide in half and roll out in a circle. Cut into 8 pie-shaped pieces. Brush with melted butter and roll up into crescent roll. Let rise until doubled and bake.

title: meat loaf masterpiece
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
If desired, form a groove lengthwise along top of loaf 1/2 inch in depth and pour additional barbecue sauce in groove.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into bowl. Mix in pudding. Add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Put in bowl and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the margarine and brown sugar in a large bowl. When creamy, add the egg, molasses and milk.
Measure the remaining ingredients and add to bowl.
Stir mixture well.

title: pink cloud punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour in plastic containers and freeze.
Thaw in the refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours before serving. ALTERNATE WAY TO PREPARE. Place partially softened sherbet and ice cream in punch bowl. Gradually add carbonated beverages.

title: hot bean casserole
directions: Brown meat, add onions and cook until tender.
Mix in large bowl meat mixture, soups, beans and tomatoes.
Layer in casserole (greased):
half of meat mixture, chips, cheese, repeat.
Brown in 400 degree oven until golden brown on top and thoroughly heated.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring 1 # 2 can of crushed pineapple to a boil.
Add a 3 ounce package of apricot jello.
Cool until thick.
Prepare 1 box (2 packages) Dream Whip according to package.
Mix 1 8 ounce package of softened cream cheese with 5 tablespoons milk.
Fold the cream cheese and Dream Whip into the jello mixture and chill.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and vegetables.
Add soup as it comes out of the can.
Top with fried onion rings.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake additional 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: funny face cookies
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
When plump, squeeze dry and use for decorating.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light lemon colored.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all but first 4 ingredients and almonds for the dressing. Add to the chopped chicken, celery, grapes, oranges and almonds. Toss lightly.

title: roast pork loin and dressing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray oblong baking dish with Pam.
Place roast (bone down) in dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast in oven 20 to 30 minutes per pound or until done.
Last 30 minutes of roasting time, cover roast lightly with foil.
Place cornbread dressing lightly around roast and return to oven, for remaining 30 minutes.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: Drain broccoli; set aside.
Combine 1 1/2 cups milk, margarine, salt, pepper and onion in 4 cup glass dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup milk and cornmeal; mix well.
Stir into hot milk mixture slowly.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring 3 times.

title: kringles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight (makes for easier handling).
Take 1 rounded teaspoonful of dough and roll into the shape of a pencil (about 5 to 6-inches long), then shape into a figure 8 or whatever shape you desire.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (no longer).
They will look light in color.
tags: baking powder for each c. flour

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Blend or beat and let stand 24 hours.
This equals one 14 ounce can Eagle Brand milk and can be used in such.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Mix ingredients.
Seal tightly and bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender.
Serve with white rice or egg noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Add browned sausage.
Blend eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian ham 'n' potatoes
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In large skillet or heavy pan, brown ham in 2 teaspoons margarine; remove.
In same skillet, brown potatoes and cook onion and peppers with thyme in remaining 4 teaspoons margarine until tender.

title: cream of lettuce soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and leek; saute for 5 minutes without letting them brown.
Stir in flour, combining it well with onion and leek.
Add lettuce, frozen peas and chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool a little. Blend in the cream. Puree in blender.
Return to saucepan.
Reheat to serve, or serve well chilled, with a dollop of sour cream, if you wish.

title: old-fashioned chess pie
directions: Heat sugars, flour, margarine and milk until completely dissolved.
Cool.
Beat 3 egg yolks and 1 whole egg well; add vanilla.
Add to cooled sugar mixture and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Begin at 350° for 15 minutes, then lower to 250°.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: swiss lettuce
directions: When bacon is browned, add other ingredients and heat to boiling point.
Pour over washed lettuce.
Slice hard-cooked eggs may be added to make salad extra delicious.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put soda in applesauce and let stand until ready to mix into cake.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs (unbeaten).
Add applesauce, then 2 cups flour, which has been sifted with spices. Add raisins and nuts that have been rolled in the other 2 cups flour.
Bake in 325° oven in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Stir until blended.
Stir in 2 teaspoons sugar; set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, onion, dill weed, baking powder, salt, 2 tablespoons sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl; turn to bring grease side up.
Cover.
Let rise to double in size.
Punch down.
Turn out only lightly floured surface; knead a few times.
Divide into 2 equal portions.
Shape into loaves in two well greased loan pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pans to rack.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Brown in butter almonds and sesame seed.
Sprinkle seasoning package over salad.

title: sweet pickled beets
directions: Cook very young, small green beans (whole) for 10 minutes. Chill in ice water.
Pack in pint jars.
Add to each jar:

title: christmas stars
directions: In a large mixer bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla and almond extract until well mixed.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough onto lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut out dough with star-shaped cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Cool on wire racks.
Ice and decorate as desired.

title: baked lemon pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper and dredge in flour. Brown chops in oil.
Arrange in baking dish with a lemon slice on each.
Mix catsup, water and brown sugar.
Pour over chops.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
If sauce cooks down too much, you may need to add a little water.

title: easy low-fat chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add beans, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Stir in chili powder (salt, if desired), pepper and remaining water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Makes 7 servings (11 grams protein; 1 gram fat and 0 cholesterol).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together softened butter and both sugars; beat well. Add vanilla and eggs; beat well. Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.

title: refreshing fruit pizza
directions: Drain juice from pineapple chunks into a small bowl.
Slice bananas into juice; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cookie dough according to package directions.
Lightly grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Press dough into pizza pan about 1/8-inch thick.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Cool on a rack.

title: slush punch
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and water.
Add jello and stir well. Add extract, pineapple juice and water.
Mix well.
Freeze at least overnight.
Thaw 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Serves 40. Makes 2 gallons.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Mix soup, mayo, curry powder and lemon juice.
Layer broccoli in bottom of baking dish; cover with chicken.
Spread sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sauce.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: col cannon
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as normal.
Saute cabbage in butter with the salt and pepper.
Add to mashed potatoes.
Whip until mixed.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak cut up cucumbers in lime and water for 12 hours or overnight.
Next, wash 3 times in clean water and soak in ice water for 3 hours.
Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Add cucumbers and soak for 5 or 6 hours or overnight. Bring mixture and cucumbers to a boil after soaking and simmer for 35 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken chasseurs
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and thyme in plastic bag. Shake pieces of chicken in seasoned flour mixture and brown thoroughly in margarine in skillet.

title: chili
directions: Brown together the hamburger, green pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Add the tomato paste and 3 cans of water.
Stir. Add the tomato sauce.
Stir in the beans in chili sauce.
Add the spices.
Cook in crock-pot on low for at least 1 hour or more.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: potato pizza
directions: In a bowl, toss together potatoes, onion and oil.
Stir in red pepper, garlic, parsley, salt, rosemary and pepper.
Brush a 12-inch pizza pan with oil.
Spread pan with potato mix.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or until tender, brown and crisp.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake 5 to 8 minutes longer or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, sugar and salad oil.
Stir well and let stand several hours.
When ready to serve, add green pepper, celery, onion and pimentos.

title: chocolate confetti balls
directions: Mix crumbs and candies.
Scoop ice cream into 4 balls.
Roll each in crumb mixture.
Place in serving dish.
Serve immediately or freeze until serving time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: happy dog "bone" biscuits
directions: You will also need a bone-shaped cookie cutter.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put all ingredients in blender.
Put milk in first.
Mix until all ingredients are blended completely. Pour in 10-inch solid pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Turn oven down to 350° and bake until brown 25 to 35 minutes. Will puff up while baking, but flatten out when out of oven.

title: chili cornbread bake
directions: Heat chili in 2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Combine egg and milk in small bowl.
Add corn bread mix.
Pour over chili.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: garlic spread
directions: Blend butter, garlic powder and paprika in small bowl until smooth.
Spread on rolls.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add chili or taco seasoning and water.
Simmer until blended.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Spread softened cream cheese on top of beef mixture.
Cube Monterey Jack cheese over cream cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or place covered in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes on High.
The beef may be browned in the same dish in microwave.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange raw, quartered potatoes in pan.
In a bowl, stir together oil, garlic, rosemary, thyme, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes. Toss to coat.
Bake, uncovered, about 25 minutes, stirring often, until brown and tender.
Serves 8.
Contains 126 calories per serving.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings in skillet until tender (do not brown).
Stir in celery, brown sugar, molasses, tomato sauce, chili sauce, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cut off greens. Do not cut too close to beet. It will bleed. Wash beets. Do not cut up. Cook till tender in boiling water, about 30 minutes. Cool. Peel and slice. Put in clean pot. Add about 1-2 cups water. Simmer on low heat to make red liquid.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in greased casserole dish.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix butter and eggs together until well combined. Add buttermilk and vanilla and mix well. Combine flour, sugar and salt and stir into the liquid. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake until set and lightly browned, 40 to 45 minutes. Let cool to room temperature on a rack. Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Heat whipping cream and Parmesan cheese together until melted. Mix all ingredients together.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in frying pan. Add onion and celery. Saute until clear. Remove from heat. Mix with soup, cheese and broccoli. Last, add rice. Put in baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in taco sauce, beans and 1 cup cheese. Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top in a ring.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: baked chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken in large pan; sprinkle with lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Allow chicken to bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.
In bowl, mix honey Dijon, peas and pecans together.
Add to chicken; cook until chicken is done.

title: california 7 layer dip(taco and pizza dip)
directions: Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Layer on platter:
bean dip, avocado, sour cream and mayonnaise mix, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Top with cheeses.
Serve with taco chips or corn chips.

title: marinated pretzels
directions: Break pretzels up. In another bowl blend olive oil, ranch mix, and garlic powder. Pour over pretzels let set 1 hr. Mix every 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°. spread on a baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes cool and serve.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend in blender, Blue cheese and cream cheese.
Add heavy cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in with spoon 1/4 cup additional Blue cheese, crumbled into large chunks.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Cut strips of bacon into 3 parts.
Wrap 3-4 beans with bacon strip and secure with a toothpick.
Place bundles into baking dish and pour dressing over them.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbling.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill in fridge overnight.
May also use commercial Italian salad dressing if you prefer.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend eggs and cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla; blend until semi-smooth.
Add sour cream until smooth and creamy. Butter bottom and sides of spring pan.
Put in graham cracker crumbs (any recipe on boxed crumbs is okay) bottom and half way up sides.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Shut off oven after 1 hour and leave cheesecake in for 1 more hour.
Remove and refrigerate.
Best if done 24 hours prior to serving.
Cover top with cherries, raspberries or blueberries if desired.
Yummy!

title: mocha-pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Dissolve coffee powder in water (mixture will be thick).
Beat butter and brown sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and coffee mixture.
Stir in flour until blended.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut crosswise in 8 even strips.
Cut strips in thirds.
Makes 24.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and biscuits in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in well-greased pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: blue cheese mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate until use.
Use as a dip, on crackers, or my favorite, as a steak sauce.

title: cheesy ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Add flour and seasonings, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add ham and potatoes, tossing gently.
Spoon into a greased 2 quart shallow baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat chicken in large skillet which has been coated with nonstick cooking spray over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in bell pepper and onion. Cook about 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are slightly crisp.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Stir in tomatoes, soup and seasoning.
Stir remaining ingredients in medium bowl until blended.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serves 10.

title: diet tangy potato topper
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 cup plain yogurt and 1 tablespoon of parsley. Serve over baked potato.
Makes 2/3 cup.
Contains 11 calories per tablespoon.

title: dump cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to the box.
Grease cake pan.
Pour in can of peaches; spread evenly on pan.
Pour cake batter on peaches.
Add chopped nuts to batter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: For crust, in a bowl, combine flour, nuts and brown sugar.
Add melted butter.
Toss to combine.
Spread mixture in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Spread 2/3 of the crust mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: aunt ethel's spoon bread
directions: Scald milk and add water and ground cornmeal.
Stir constantly. Cool.
Add salt and egg yolks, mixing well.
Heat oven to 350°. Melt oleo in baking dish and coat sides.
Beat egg whites until peaks form and fold into corn meal mixture.
Put in baking dish and set in pan of hot water.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour or until set.

title: crab spread appetizer
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on plate or tray.
Crumble crab over top.
Pour cocktail sauce on top and serve immediately. To be spread on crackers.
This should be prepared just before serving.

title: meat loaf with applesauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in order in which they are given.
Butter a loaf tin and pack them into it.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: browned butter crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 10-inch tube pan with Baker's Joy. Coat pan evenly with 2/3 cup of nuts; sprinkle nuts with 1 tablespoon sugar. Set aside. In a small saucepan, melt butter, stirring occasionally, until golden brown. In large bowl, combine browned butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and soda. Add to butter mixture alternately with milk. Pour in greased pan. Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake 40 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: brownie bites
directions: Melt sweet chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Stir and cool.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Beat 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Stir in chocolate well.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
On lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle.
Place a 9-inch pie plate.
Turn under edge; flute.
Bake 5 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/4 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread 1 cup caramel mixture on bottom of crust, set remaining caramel mixture aside.
Mix pumpkin, remaining evaporated milk, sugar, eggs, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves until well blended; pour over caramel mixture in crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; continue baking 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Stir reserved caramel mixture and milk over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Spread 1/4 cup over top of pie.
Serve remaining caramel sauce with pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eggnog bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Combine eggnog, egg and butter.
Add to the dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Add nuts and fruit.
Bake in a loaf pan 60 to 70 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool on a wire rack. Freezes well.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Coat a wok with oil and place over medium-high until hot. Add peas, carrots, chicken and tofu; stir-fry 4 minutes or until chicken is done.
Add wine mixture, green onions and peppers. Stir-fry one minute.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients together, mixing flour with the soup (to prevent lumps).
Pour over cooked potatoes.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or 30 minutes in microwave.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar with water.
Bring to a boil.
When thickened, add wild strawberry jello mix.
Add strawberries.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Then pour into crust.
Add Cool Whip.

title: cheryl's oatmeal, walnut, raisin, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix will be hard to stir.
Make balls or drop teaspoon size drops on cookie sheet.
Drop about 2 inches apart.
Cook approximately 8 minutes.

title: strawberry candies
directions: Combine milk, coconut, 1 package Jell-O, almonds, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Shape mixture in strawberries.
Roll candies in remaining Jell-O, coating thoroughly.
Let candy dry until firm. Make leaves with icing on top of candies.
Yields 48.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Let set at room temperature at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: "pop-pop's" outstanding baked beans
directions: Place beans in a 3-quart casserole (round, oblong, glass or disposable aluminum, whatever, just as long as it's ovenproof). Cook bacon slices in frying pan until crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Break into nice size bits and pieces.
Discard 1/2 the bacon drippings.
Pour remaining drippings into the casserole. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir until blended with a wooden spoon.

Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes, until it's heated through. If you like a nice crust over the beans, don't stir them. If you like your beans without a crust, stir them once or twice during cooking time.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water.
Add enough water to achieve a smooth consistency.
By teaspoon or tablespoon, drop into deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with fish or greens.

title: praline candy
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together to 236°; remove from heat. Add oleo.
Beat and add lots of nuts.
Drop from spoon.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and place in 3-quart casserole. Cover with chicken.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Melt butter and stir in cracker crumbs.
Top casserole with cracker crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit and save 1 1/2 cups juices.
Mix sugar, salt and flour in medium saucepan.
Add 1 1/2 cups fruit juice and butter. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Place fruit in a 2-quart buttered oblong baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: best cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan. With all ingredients at room temperature, mix all in one large bowl until well blended.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and open the oven door; leave cake in for 1 more hour.
Chill.
May top with apricot or strawberry preserves.

title: speedy doughnuts
directions: Separate biscuit dough.
Cut hole in center of each biscuit. Fry biscuits and holes, a few at a time, in 1/2 to 1 inch of hot shortening or oil (375°), or use deep-fryer.
Cook until golden brown, about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with sugar or cinnamon sugar, or ice with homemade or prepared chocolate icing.
Serve while warm.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Cool.
Add Equal to strawberries.
Add strawberries to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into cooked or graham cracker crust.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Oil a 4-quart casserole dish.
Layer:
ground beef with onions, cream of mushroom soup, broccoli and Tater Tots.
Repeat until dish is full.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: country corn chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic and celery.
Return water to a boil and add bouillon and seasonings. Cover and simmer over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, but not mushy.
Cool slightly.
Remove 2 cups of potatoes from stock and set aside.
Blend remaining chowder in small increments.
Reheat over low heat.
Add corn and reserved potatoes.
Simmer, stirring to insure that chowder does not stick for 5 minutes.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except yams, in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Arrange yams in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: new york chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend together all of the ingredients.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.
Brush chicken or meat with mixture while barbecuing or cooking.
Yields approximately 2 cups.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft but not brown. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and puree in a blender.
Add peanut butter and cream, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Return to low heat but do not boil.
Serve, garnished with peanuts.
This soup is also good served ice cold.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender.
Cool and cut into bite-size pieces.
In a very large bowl, stir salad dressing, vinegar, mustard, lemon pepper and dill.
Gently fold in potatoes, eggs, artichoke and onion.
Cover and chill 4 to 24 hours.
Makes 16 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except parsley and cayenne pepper.
Top with parsley sprigs and dash of cayenne pepper. Serve as dip for corn chips or potato chips.

title: layered lettuce
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and set aside.
Layer lettuce, peas, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Top first with mayonnaise mixture, then bacon and then Parmesan cheese.
Chill overnight.

title: reese's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix brownie mix according to directions on package.
Divide brownie mix into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 15 minutes or until pie crust is brown.
Combine peanut butter and 8 ounces cream cheese with 1 cup milk until smooth.
Gradually add rest of milk. Add pudding and blend until thick.
Pour over baked brownie mix in pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Sprinkle with cut up Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients in a large storage container.
For each cup of hot water, use 1/3 cup of mix.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
In small pan, mix well sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Stir in orange juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute. Remove and stir in butter. Drain carrots and toss with sauce.
Garnish with slices of orange.

title: oven barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut and remove tips from chicken wings.
In saucepan mix sauces, 1 tablespoon butter, garlic powder and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Let simmer for 20 minutes while wings are cooking. Place butter (1 stick) on cookie sheet and melt in oven.
Lay wings on melted butter to coat both sides.
Place back in oven for 20 minutes at 325°.
Remove cookie sheet from oven and pour 1/2 of barbecue sauce over wings; return to oven and bake another 30 minutes.
Turn on broiler for a few minutes to brown.
Serve with leftover sauce.
Can be put into crock-pot when cooking process is complete and kept warm.
Super!
Always a hit!

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped beef and let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Stir in soup to a creamy consistency.
Add milk, cheese and onion.
Stir gently and add macaroni.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Store in refrigerator, covered, for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Alternate layers of oysters and crumbs in an 8-inch square pan, sprinkling each layer with a dash of salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix together oyster liquid with milk and pour over casserole, then top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix above ingredients except cake mix; place in refrigerator. Let stand overnight. Bake cake mix. Let cool. Spread on filling. Sprinkle top and sides with flaked coconut if desired.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients into a stiff dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut in strips.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° until light brown.

title: cheese tasters
directions: Cream butter; add flour and next 3 ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cereal.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Place balls about 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten each ball with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool completely on wire racks.
Yield:
5 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet kosher dill pickles
directions: Place pickles back in jar and cover with onion and pickling spice.
Boil together the water, sugar and vinegar and pour over pickles in jar.
Seal and refrigerate for a few days.

title: rice with mushrooms and parmesan cheese
directions: Prepare mushrooms and onion.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a saucepan.
Add onion; cook briefly, stirring.
Add mushrooms. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; stir.
Add rice; stir to blend. Add bay leaf and chicken broth; bring to simmer.
Cover; cook for 17 minutes.
Swirl in remaining tablespoon of butter and the cheese.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Pour into three 8-inch prepared round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook the rice in dressing and water mixed together.
Cool then add frozen peas, olives, onions, celery, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Layer crescent rolls in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix and let chill.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and crumbled bread and let soak.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Shape into 1/2 inch thick patties.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in skillet.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over fried patties.
Heat until bubbly. Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
Take 1 stick of butter, melt in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture over butter.
Mix 1 cup of self-rising flour with 1 cup of milk.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash 12 bananas with a fork.
Beat 8 eggs with a fork.
Put in first bowl and mix.
In second bowl put flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add banana mixture to second bowl and stir well.
Put in a greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious cake
directions: Mix oil and eggs with cake mix and beat together.
Add nuts and coconut; beat well.
Fold in thawed strawberries and blend in well.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) layers at 350° until done.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: In a large pot, melt butter; cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Add water, potatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or until potatoes are done.
In small bowl, make paste of flour by adding a few drops of water.
Pour into pot.
Add corn (undrained) and ham.
Heat through, but do not boil as it will curdle.
Enjoy!

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine ingredients into large pot (6 quart).
Cook on high for 3 hours then turn down heat to simmer for 2 hours.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts of spicy clam chowder.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter. Microwave for 3 minutes or until melted, stirring well, then carefully add cereal, peanuts and raisins.
Mix well.
In a brown paper bag, pour in confectioners sugar carefully.
Add the coated mixture, then shake! shake! and shake!
Store in airtight container.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking dish with Pam cooking spray. Dip chicken in butter; coat with remaining combined ingredients. Place in prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until tender.

title: oven toasted pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients except salt.
Mix well.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Salt to taste.
Stir often while baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain well.
Melt the margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Blend all the ingredients in the casserole. Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab rice squares with shrimp sauce
directions: Combine onion, parsley, pimento, crabmeat, eggs, milk, rice, Accent, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Put into greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Mix together soup, sour cream and Accent.
Warm over low heat.
Do not boil!
Pour over crabmeat mixture.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Combine cookies and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze 30 minutes.
Top cookie layer with softened ice cream. Freeze 30 minutes.
Combine condensed milk, syrup and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Add vanilla.
Put over layer of ice cream.
Frost with Cool Whip. Serves 12 or more.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until lightly browned; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, catsup and seasoning.
Alternate layers of meat and cheese in a 2-quart casserole, ending with cheese.
Place rolls around edge of casserole. Bake at 400° until rolls are golden brown. Serve hot.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Bring bouillon cubes, onion, carrots, celery and water to a boil and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 20 minutes longer.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and cheese. Stir until well blended and cheese is melted.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan combine sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil; then add peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Bring to a boil again; then add dry oats.
At this time coconut, raisins or nuts may also be added.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or a cookie sheet.
Cool before eating.
Makes approximately 40 to 60 cookies.

title: chicken in jade
directions: Mix in bowl the egg white and cornstarch.
Add cut up chicken and coat.
Set aside.
Make sauce and put aside.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling and pineapple together in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix well and spread over bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over bottom.
Do not stir.
Pour melted butter over top of dry cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream or icing.

title: edra's apple pie
directions: Grease
bottom
of a 12 x 12-inch pan and place some of the apple
slices
on
the
bottom.
Mix juice and tapioca in sauce and
let stand for 10 minutes.
Add the remaining apple slices
to the
juice
and heat.
Pour over the apples in the bottom of the pan.
Spread cake mix over the apple mixture and spoon
melted margarine over the cake mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain thoroughly.
Stir in egg and butter.
Mix mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon hot water and then add to macaroni.
Add cheese, reserving small amount to sprinkle over top.
Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish. Add milk.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix.
Make into balls and fry in Crisco oil until brown. Place in baking dish.
Mix 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can tomato sauce.
Pour over meat; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buckeyes peanut butter creams
directions: Knead all ingredients until sticky. Roll in large marble-size balls. Cool and dip in dipping chocolate. Cool and package.

title: sea biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Put all ingredients in the mixing bowl; mix with a fork until the mixture has lumps the size of peas.
Work the dough with your hands until it is smooth.
Divide the dough into 28 to 30 small pieces, about the size of marbles. Roll each piece of dough into a ball, then flatten it with your fingers into a very thin circle.
Place the circles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until biscuits are dry and light brown around edges.
Cool; store in airtight container.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in Ziploc bag. Add biscuits and shake to coat well. Cook brown sugar and margarine on low heat until melted. Put 1/2 of biscuits in tube pan and add 1/2 of pecans and 1/2 of brown sugar mixture. Add remaining biscuits, pecans and brown sugar mixture. Sprinkle some of cinnamon and sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: washday dinner
directions: When the cupboard is getting bare and you don't know what to cook for supper, pray and ask the Lord to give you a menu or new recipe from what you have.
He will do it.
My family loves to hear that we are having an experiment for supper.

title: low-fat lemon-blueberry muffins
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice.
Stir; set aside. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk, oil, egg substitute, lemon rind and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture; stir only until all ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Spray large muffin pan with Mazola spray.
Spoon batter into tin and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with lemon juice mixture.
Bake an additional 6 to 8 minutes, until muffins are golden.
Cool.
Yield: 12 (181 calories and 5.4 fat).

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill the dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts, then roll into the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: honey muffins
directions: Sift the flour and then re-sift with baking powder and salt. Add cornmeal.
Set aside.
Combine one beaten egg, honey and melted shortening.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Fold in 1/4 chopped apple.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased muffin cups.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: punch for 80 people
directions: Pour pineapple juice, orange juice, apple juice and ginger ale over ice.
Add sherbet.
Garnish with cherries or any fruit slices (optional).
Use 4 ounce cups.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix and stir first 5 ingredients over medium heat until all is melted.
Remove from heat and add the remaining 4 ingredients. Mix and chill.

title: rutabagas
directions: Peel and slice rutabagas.
Cook uncovered in boiling water until tender.
Season with salt, margarine, lemon juice and parsley.

title: not-so-smothered chicken*
directions: Dredge chicken breasts in flour until fully coated.
Melt butter in heavy skillet or electric skillet.
Saute chicken breasts until golden brown on both sides.
After browning, add celery and olives distributing evenly over chicken breasts.
Add water and lower heat.
Cover skillet and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove cover and continue simmering for 10 more minutes or until done.
Add water as necessary during simmering to maintain a moist, gravy-like base.
Best served with rice or whipped potatoes with a side dish of a steamed fresh vegetable such as broccoli or asparagus.
Drizzle a good portion of gravy onto rice or whipped potatoes.
Yields 5-6 servings.

title: white fish fillets
directions: Place fish in 1 1/2-quart oblong dish.
Place fish in the dish and brush with melted butter and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover.
Cook in microwave oven 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes. Recipe yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: soy-marinated chicken
directions: Mince garlic, ginger, parsley and onion.
Place in large plastic container.
Stir in the soy sauce, chicken broth, sugar, vinegar, sherry and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add chicken breasts and turn to coat in marinade.
Cover and refrigerate, turning once, overnight or up to 24 hours.
Remove chicken and pat dry.
Place chicken on hot grill.
Cover and cook (basting occasionally with marinade) for approximately 30 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries.
Add 1 beaten egg, 2 or 3 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook until thick. Cool; add fruit, nuts, and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip and freeze.

title: hot crab cocktail spread
directions: Combine cream cheese with milk and Worcestershire sauce. Drain and flake crabmeat.
Add to cream cheese mixture along with chopped green onion.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, brown sugar and sugar until creamy. Add vanilla and eggs. Mix well. Add dry ingredients and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° on center rack for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry jellied salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot orange juice. Stir in sugar.
Cool to slight gel and combine fruits and nuts in syrupy gel mixture and let chill.
Serves 20 to 24 people.
May be frozen.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix well the peanut butter, oleo and powdered sugar.
Form into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate together.
Use a toothpick to dip balls in melted chocolate and paraffin.
Let them dry on cookie sheet.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool slightly.
Peel and cube. Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add diced onion to bacon grease until tender, but not brown.
Stir flour and seasonings into mixture.
Add water and vinegar, stirring until thickened.
Add potatoes and bacon and toss lightly.

title: oatmeal whoopie pies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add salt, flour, oatmeal, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add soda water last.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fill with Vanilla Filling.

title: jackie's cool summer salad
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, eggs and reserved juices.
Bring to almost boiling.
Pour thickened juices over fruit and macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Two hours before serving, mix in Cool Whip.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken in 3 quarts water until cooked completely. Place chicken breasts to the side. Cook noodles in remaining chicken broth. Drain. Piece chicken up in noodles. Cut cheese up in pieces. Put remaining ingredients all in pot together and cook until cheese is melted. Ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixer; cut in shortening.
Mix egg, vinegar and water together.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Divide into 4 equal portions.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: broccoli flounder roll-ups
directions: Roll each fillet around a broccoli spear; secure with toothpick.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over fish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sliced tomatoes with basil
directions: Slice tomatoes into round disc and spread on flat plate. Sprinkle with basil and olive oil.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan real good. Don't need to flour pan. Sprinkle coconut on bottom of pan, then add chopped nuts. Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour over coconut and pecans. In small pan, melt butter until soft. Add cream cheese and sifted powdered sugar. Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix and swirl with the cake mix until all is mixed in. Do not touch bottom of pan while swirling. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done. It will puff up and not look done. That's why it looks like an earthquake hit it. Real good, though.

title: garden pizza
directions: Bake pie crust flat on cookie sheet until medium brown.
Let cool.

title: crispy rice snacks
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add crispy rice cereal.
Using waxed paper, press the mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 squares.

title: burritos
directions: Brown meat.
Remove 1/2 of meat to use with chili mix.
Add taco seasoning as directed on pkg. with the remaining meat.
When cooked, add green chilies and refried beans.
Roll tortillas with meat mixture.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Layer burritos in pan.
Fix chili mix according to directions on pkg.
Pour over burritos and top with grated cheese and chopped onions.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Check often - don't overcook.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, cook until tender and drain.
Beat softened cream cheese with cream.
Add hot potatoes and blend well.
Add butter and seasonings.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix in the order shown.
Mix condensed milk with Cool Whip, then stir in the pie filling.
Finally, add the pineapple and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.
It's soooooo good.

title: rice, green beans and ham casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix together green beans, soup, grated cheese and diced ham.
Add sauteed onions, bell pepper and cooked rice.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Remove the sausage meat from the casings.
Fry the sausage meat and the onion in olive oil until the sausage crumbles and the onion is soft.
Add just enough marinara sauce to the sausage and onion to make a thick mixture.
Cook and drain pasta following package directions.
Preheat oven to 375°.	Cover the bottom of a deep baking dish with a layer of cooked pasta.
Cover pasta with a thin layer of the sauce and sausage mixture.
Add a thin layer of cottage cheese.
Next, sprinkle bread crumbs over the cottage cheese and cover the bread crumbs with a layer of Mozzarella. Then repeat the layers, making sure that Mozzarella is the layer at the top.
Bake covered for 45 minutes.

title: smothered steak(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Sprinkle each steak with seasoned salt and dredge with flour. Brown in skillet in small amount of oil or shortening.
Arrange in baking pan or dish.
If necessary, more than one layer may be placed in pan.
Top each piece with as much onion as you like and as many mushrooms as you can afford.
Add green pepper if you like.

title: cocktail
directions: Put ingredients into gallon jar and fill with water.
Sugar to taste.

title: peach and pear salad
