directions: Mix softened cream cheese, nuts and orange juice together. Roll cheese into small balls.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: basic pound cake
directions: Cream the butter with electric mixer until fluffy. Cream in the sugar. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time, on medium-high speed. Batter should have the consistency of heavy whipped cream. Stir in vanilla and lemon extracts.
Sift flour with salt twice.
Beat butter into mixture at lowest speed.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Fold into cake batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake in a preheated 325° oven for 60 minutes.

title: apple cake with sauce
directions: Mix sugar with apples; let stand until sugar is dissolved. Add beaten egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into apple mixture.
Add nuts last.
Bake in 8-inch square pan for 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: unbaked blueberry pie
directions: Cook 1/4 cup berries in 1 1/4 cups water.
When cooked, strain berries from water and throw berries away.
Then add 3/4 cup sugar to the water, lemon juice and salt.
Mix cornstarch with 4 tablespoons water and thicken.
When cool, add the 3 1/4 cups of berries to the thickening.
Put in baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: scott's squares
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients plus the egg yolks. Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Combine the dry ingredients and the creamed mixture and mix until it resembles cookie dough.
Wet your fingers and spread mixture into a 10 x 15-inch glass dish.
Whip the egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add the brown sugar.
Spread over the top of dough. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake until brown.
Let cool and cut into 24 squares.

title: punch
directions: Pour soda over softened sherbet.

title: rice krispies snacks
directions: Mix softened margarine with cheese.
When well blended, add Rice

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: turkey sausage soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar.
Sift together soda, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Add rest of ingredients to the eggs and sugar mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in shallow dish.
Coat each breast with cooking spray.
Dredge in cereal mixture.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray and coat chicken again with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: pecan stuffing
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Add turkey giblets and brown on all sides.
Cool.
Dice cooked giblets and set aside.
Mix bread crumbs, salt, peppers and spices.
Stir in the 1/2 cup melted butter, boiling water and honey. Cool. Add the beaten eggs.
Mix well. Stir in the cooked giblets and pecans. Bake.

title: oriental fried peppers and onions
directions: Slice
tops from peppers.
Cut into narrow strips.
Cut onion into rings.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Cook vegetables	 in skillet.
Add
rest.
Cook,
covered,
minutes. Uncover. Continue
cooking,	stirring frequently, with wooden spoon	until moisture evaporates and vegetables start to brown in remaining oil.
Vegetables should remain firm and crunchy.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle over margarine the graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut, Eagle Brand milk and nuts.
Place in order given. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons by dropping into hot Wesson oil.
Brown.
Remove from oil and drain.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix blended crushed Oreos and butter.
Press into pie pan. Whip the whipping cream.
Add marshmallow cream and creme de menthe.
Pour into pie shell.

title: garlic grits
directions: Place eggs
in	cup,
then completely fill the cup with water; mix well.

title: molly e.'s hot and sour soup
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add mushrooms, tofu, shoots and chicken. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Combine cornstarch with water; add gradually to thicken. Remove from heat.
Drizzle beaten egg slowly into soup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple and nuts; cut in a blender until consistency of soft butter.
Mix room warm cheese and all other ingredients except parsley.
Mix thoroughly with hands and place in small round bowl that has been sprayed with Pam. Refrigerate overnight.
Take chilled ball out.
Roll in parsley flakes and return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pecan log
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to a hard boil in cold water. Add the butter and vanilla; let cool.
Beat.
When it is hard, shape into a log; roll in pecans.

title: mock sweetbreads
directions: Mix all but soup and water together.
Make into cakes.
Lay on wax paper for 1/2 hour or longer.
Brown in shortening.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour soup diluted with water over.
Bake in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves so good.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 cup pina colada mix, rum, oil and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool slightly.
Blend confectioners sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons pina colada mix in bowl; drizzle over cake.
Yields 16 servings.

title: doughnuts (raised)
directions: Make sponge.
Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm liquid.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour and beat well.
Cover and set aside to rise in warm place for about 1 hour or until bubbles burst on top.
Add to this the butter and sugar (creamed), mace, well beaten egg, the remainder of the flour to make a moderately soft dough, and the salt.
Knead lightly.
Place in a well-greased bowl. Cover and allow to rise again in warm place for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix and pat in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: football casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add onions, tomatoes, ketchup, worcestershire sauce and green pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to pkg. directions, drain.
Combine with meat mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend in soup.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Spread seeds in large shallow pan.
Mix butter with garlic salt and drizzle over seeds.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter to a soft ball stage (243 degrees), stirring frequently, then add marshmallow, nuts, chips and vanilla. Stir until chips are melted.

title: lucille's corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together; place in greased deep casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carol's coconut cake
directions: Sift flour, each kind separately 3 times.
Measure correct amount of each and sift with baking powder and soda.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff and set aside.
Beat yolks with sugar, add oil, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour mixture in small amounts, blending well.
Add egg whites.
Pour into 4 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured well.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: frozen strawberry banana salad
directions: Stir together pie filling, ice cream and lemon juice.
Stir in bananas and nuts.
Turn into 8 individual molds.
Freeze firm several hours or overnight.
Place in refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Unmold onto lettuce-lined plates.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with mixer, add sugar slowly until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and soda three times.
Add alternately with sour cream to egg mixture, beginning with & ending with flour mixture.
Add Griffin's Vanilla & Griffin's Coconut.
Pour into 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hr. and 30 mins.
(You can use a Bundt pan.)

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add to oil.
Beat well.
Add sugar, beating again.
Add carrots, apples, nuts, pineapple and vanilla. Beat again.
Fold in sifted flour, soda, salt and baking powder gradually, beating well.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef tips in mushroom sauce
directions: Put meat in crock-pot.	Pour soup and onion soup mix over meat. Add Sprite or 7-Up.
Cover and cook all day on low or for at least 4 hours on high or until meat is tender. Turn off and let sit for 30 minutes before serving. Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion and seasonings and add 6 cups water to soup kettle and cover; simmer 2 hours.

title: buttermilk cinnamon bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. In small bowl, combine oil, and 1-1/2 cups sugar. Add buttermilk and eggs; mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill two greased 8 x 4 x 2 inch loaf pans about 1/3 full. Combine cinnamon and remaining sugar; sprinkle 1/2 over the batter. Top with remaining batter, cinnamon and sugar. Swirl batter with a knife. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: oklahoma prairie fire(serves 6)
directions: Mix first three ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with sliced cheese. Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish, fondue pot or on warming tray with Doritos.

title: onion sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion rings in oil until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Makes 1 cup.
Serve hot.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop or coarse grate cabbage, pepper and onion.
Add sugar. Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and salt; bring to a full boil.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage mixture; toss together.
Seal in airtight containers.
Do not stir or uncover for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator for a week or more.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a glass bowl or plastic container. Add chicken wings.
Coat all the wings with marinade.
Then refrigerate and let it marinate at least 3 hours.
Periodically, stir the wings around.
May be marinated overnight.
Then cook the wings on the grill, under the broiler or in a 400° oven, turning at least once to brown both sides.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cocoa.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and eggs. Add flour.
Add cocoa mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 14-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole #2
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: beet jello salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into mold.
Let set.

title: chinatown chicken simmer
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Mix 1/4 cup juice with cornstarch.
Brown chicken well in oil; sprinkle with salt.
Add garlic, onion and ginger; saute.

title: bishop's cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Fill 2 (8 x 4-inch) greased loaf pans 3/4 full and bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add the corn syrup, coconut, pineapple, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
(If top seems to brown too quickly, cover lightly with foil.)
Cool pie on wire rack.
Cool before cutting.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour mixture on crumbs.
Spread rest of crumbs on top.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff (not dry); set aside.
Beat yolks; add sugar and milk, beating until well blended.
Add vanilla. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into cups or glasses and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Makes 4 to 6 small servings.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine sugar, half and half and salt in a deep 3-quart bowl. Mix well. Stir in butter. Microwave at High for 7 to 9 1/2 minutes or until mixture reaches soft-ball stage (235° on candy thermometer), stirring once after 3 minutes of cooking. Stir in pecans. Cool about 1 minute. Beat by hand with wooden spoon until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken, about 3 minutes. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper. Let stand until firm. Wrap in Saran Wrap when cool. Makes 2 dozen.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pastry.
Add top crust. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together for a wonderful dip for your fresh fruits.

title: chiffon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
In saucepan, combine pineapple and juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add dissolved gelatine.
Stir in hot water.
Pour into a large mixing bowl and refrigerate until it begins to gel (edges will be gel, but center will be liquid). Shred cheese and chop pecans.
After removing mixture from refrigerator, fold in Cool Whip, cheese and pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.
Delicious!

title: cheezy broccoli
directions: Place in baking dish in layers and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: english toffee squares
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Separate egg.
Beat yolk into butter mixture; cover and reserve white.

title: pineapple mint conserve
directions: Mix fruit and sugar, stir well and bring to boiling point. Cook hard for 1 minute.
Add coloring.
Take from stove and add pectin.
Skim well and allow to cool, stirring often.
Add flavoring and put into jars.
This is excellent served with roast lamb.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with celery, green onions, regular onions and bouillon cubes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in greased 11 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour into pan over nuts and coconut. Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar; pour over batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Cook the first 9 ingredients
in a Dutch oven until the vegetables are tender.
Meanwhile, stir
1/4 cup of the 3 cups milk into the flour, making a
paste.
Stir the paste into the vegetable
mixture and gradually
add
cups
of
milk, stirring.
Cook slowly until
mixture
is
thickened.
Add the cheese and cook very slowly, stirring gently, until the cheese melts.
Be sure to cook over
low
heat so the cheese does not burn.
Soup will be quite thick.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: salmon phyllo bites
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine salmon, peas, pimiento and cheese. Unroll phyllo sheets; cover with plastic wrap or towel.
Place one phyllo sheet on work area; brush with margarine.
Layer with 2 more sheets, brushing each with margarine.
Cut through layered sheets to make 20 rectangles.
Place heaping teaspoonful of salmon mixture in center of each rectangle.
Bring up edges of pastry, twisting together with circular motion.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle phyllo bundles with dill weed.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel on top of crust and sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate.
Stir pudding mixes into milk in medium saucepan. Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat and let cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
If desired, garnish with whipped topping, chopped pecans and drizzle with caramel.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: edwards' virginia bacon and mushroom dip(the hickory-smoked bacon is the secret!)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic in reserved drippings until soft and most of the liquid has evaporated.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper and allow to bubble on medium heat for 2 minutes; stir frequently.
Add cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce; heat on low until cheese melts. Stir in sour cream and 8 strips of crumbled bacon.
Spoon into serving bowl and garnish with remaining crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with parsley or chives.
Serve warm.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with Melba toast, bread sticks or crackers.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook roast, onion, oil, celery, salt and pepper in pressure cooker until very well done.
Break apart with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients; cook and stir until well mixed.
Serve on buns.

title: cheerio treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine until melted. Add marshmallows.
Toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave until smooth when stirred.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal; mix lightly until well coated.
Press into prepared pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cut sugar into cream cheese with pastry blender.
Add a few drops of food coloring until desired shade is reached.
Knead until smooth.
Roll into logs and cut 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick or press into candy molds by pinching off a piece of dough and rolling into a ball.
Dip in granulated sugar and press into lightly greased rubber mold.
Level off with spatula, then twist mold to release mint.
Stack between sheets of wax paper and freeze for later use if desired.
Yield:
75 mints.

title: chocolate-kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup of flour, the sugar, egg, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat until combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
If necessary, chill dough until easy to handle.

title: algia's banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham crackers and margarine and press into pie dish for crust.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, heat thoroughly the butter and sugar; add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased glass 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done; debone. Save chicken broth to cook spaghetti in. Saute green peppers and onions in about 2 teaspoons oil until soft. Boil and drain spaghetti. Add tomatoes (cut up) and soup into vegetables and chicken. Mix together. Put in large baking dish. Top with sliced Velveeta cheese. Bake about 30 minutes until cheese melts.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in shortening until golden brown.
Add 6 cups of water, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes. Serve with toast rounds and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix walnuts and raisins with a little of flour.
Add last. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in tube pan.

title: basic chicken stock
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a stockpot and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes, skimming top frequently.
Cover partially, leaving only a small opening, and simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Strain the stock into a large bowl, pressing on the solids.
Let cool slightly and refrigerate.
Remove the solidified fat from the stock before using.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix boiling water and lemon jello together; set aside.
Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs and lemon extract.
After mixing cake mix, add the jello water and pour into 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan real well.
Melt top 4 ingredients in double boiler.
Spread 1 package of miniature marshmallows and 1 (16 ounce) bag salted peanuts.
Pour melted mixture over this and stir real well.
Pat down and cool.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to lukewarm.
Add yeast softened in water.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Beat mixture thoroughly, then sift in 3 cups flour and beat well.
Knead in more flour to make it workable, but keep the dough soft.
Place dough in bowl, cover with cloth.
Place where warm.
Let rise to top of bowl; press dough down, then shape rolls and place close together in lightly buttered baking pan.
Let rise above pan.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add vinegar and water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cut beets into desired pieces and add to hot sauce.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
Just before serving, heat well and add butter.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into 6-ounce graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set. Cool and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put eggs in bowl, add sugar, shortening, milk and salt.
Mix together.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in the warm water, vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Let dough rise 1/2 hour in bowl, then put dough on a floured board, knead.
Let stand and rise for 45 minutes.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into doughnuts.
Let rise and put in hot grease until brown.
Turn over doughnuts to brown other side.
Put into glaze.

title: ray's chocolate pie
directions: Mix
and cool until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat
and
add
1/3 stick oleo and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and spread on pie. Brown.
Cool and eat.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix together and add red food coloring to make it a pretty color.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and let it stand to make it slushy.

title: chicken divan
directions: Wash pig's head meat, tongue, pork liver and heart and place in a large pot and boil until tender.
Cool.
Remove from pot and grind on a meat grinder with a clove of garlic and small onion. Season with salt and pepper to taste (1/8 teaspoon of marjoram may be added if desired).
Mix well together.
Add cooked barley or rice (about 2 cups).
Mix again.
Add enough of the soup or liquid the meat was cooked in to make it of medium consistency (about like for regular pork sausage).
Mix well.
Pack into casings, tie it and cook in the meat broth (gently) for about 45 minutes on low heat.
Remove and cool.
Tastes better if served the next day. Serve with warm sauerkraut and potatoes and rye bread.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
Add one can chopped green chilies, one chopped onion, 8 ounces shredded cheese.
Set aside. Mix soup, 1 can green chilies and sour cream.
Add one heaping tablespoonful of this soup mixture to the chicken mixture.
Stuff and roll tortillas with chicken mixture.
Place fold side down in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Top with soup, sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle 4 ounces shredded cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy - Ole!

title: rocky road peanut butter squares
directions: Heat syrup and sugar to boiling in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Immediately remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Place cereal, stirring until well coated.
Cool 2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows.
Press mixture into an ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: easy german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat in medium saucepan. Add milk, coconut, eggs and sugar until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: zesty lemon chicken
directions: Grease foil-lined pan.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place oats, paprika, oregano, salt and pepper in the blender container and mix well.
Stir in parsley.
Coat chicken in oat mixture.
Dip into milk and coat again with oat mixture.
Place on rack.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off some of the fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: scarlett sipper(punch)
directions: Combine cranapple drink, orange juice and lemon juice.
Slowly pour soda water down side of pitcher.
Stir gently and add ice cubes.

title: carrots, candied
directions: Boil carrots in plain water until tender, but still whole. Drain water.
Add other ingredients and slowly cook for about an hour until thickened.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple
juice
to
make	2 cups. Add remaining ingredients and pour into oiled mold and chill.

title: lime pineapple mold
directions: Grease
Tupperware Jell-O molds.
Mix Jell-O with hot water;
add 1 cup pineapple juice.
While warm add cream cheese and
mayonnaise.
(I
chop
my
cream
cheese up with my pastry blender.)
When
cool, add 8 slices of cut fine pineapple; whip the cream and add last.

title: spicy cajun sausage and beans
directions: In skillet, cook meat, onion and garlic until onion is tender; drain.
Add tomatoes, beans, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, or until desired consistency. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chinese green beans
directions: Cook all ingredients on High in microwave oven until crisp-tender.
Good hot or cold.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and oleo; mix well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and layer into casserole dish. Add crushed Ritz crackers for topping. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: walnut cream fudge
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to full boil, stirring.
Boil 5 minutes over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate morsels until melted, then vanilla and walnuts. Pour in greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: cherry-angel food cake
directions: Cut angel cake across in 3 layers. Add cream cheese, sugar and powdered sugar. Mix well. Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Spread between layers and top and side of cake. Spoon pie cherries all over cake. It will run down sides and in center. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream together oleo, oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternatively with buttermilk and vanilla.
Put into a 9x13 pan and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: apricot squares
directions: Combine canned apricots, 3/4 cup sugar and water; cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until slightly thickened. Cool. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream butter or margarine, gradually adding 1 cup sugar; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Press 3 cups of this crumbly mixture in bottom and halfway up sides of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread apricot mixture over crust and sprinkle rest of crumbs over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack beans lengthwise into hot, sterile pint jars (wide-mouth), leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
To each pint, add 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper or dry red chilies, 1 clove garlic and head of fresh dill or 1/2 teaspoon dill seed.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boiling.
Pour over beans, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps tight.
Process pints for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 4 pints.

title: mom's ham-bean chowder
directions: Wash beans.
Cover beans with water in a 6-quart saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let beans soak 1 hour.
Drain, reserving liquid.

Return beans to saucepot; add 4 cups reserved liquid, meat, vegetables, seasonings and chicken broth combined with enough water to measure 6 cups. Bring to a boil; simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat, bay leaf and cloves.
Cut meat off bone; return to soup.
Skim off fat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: hamburger crock-pot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesey chicken and potatoes
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken breast.
Place in baking dish (large so you have space for potatoes).
Combine all other ingredients except potatoes.
Cut potatoes into 1/2 inch slices with skin on and place at one end of the dish.
Spread sauce over chicken and potatoes and bake at 375° for 30-40 minutes or until done.

title: brown sugar coconut pie
directions: Mix corn syrup, brown
sugar
and
butter
in
saucepan. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add well beaten eggs in thin stream, beating constantly.
Add
vanilla and coconut.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° until brown.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Whip together egg white and cold water.
Coat pecans with egg white mixture.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Check constantly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip heavy whipping cream until stiff.
Add mayonnaise and sugar; beat again.
Slice bananas, apple and pineapple into bite-size pieces and add.
Stir in marshmallows and add cherries for color/garnish.

title: indonesian fruit salad
directions: Combine bananas, oranges and dates in a large bowl.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Add pineapple to fruit. Combine juice with wine vinegar, curry powder, salt and salad oil. Shake well; pour over fruit and marinate about 1/2 hour.
Arrange on platter with crisp greens.
Spoon cottage cheese on top and fruit over all.
Top salad with peanuts and serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients a few minutes, add water and bring to a slow boil.
Add Kitchen Bouquet until soup is an appetizing color. Add a few bay leaves, salt and pepper and simmer a few hours. Discard bay leaf when removing soup from heat.
Lightly toast the French bread slices.
Place in bottom of crock, laddle soup over and cover with the cheese of your choice.
Place under the broiler until cheese is lightly browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine hash browns, sour cream and mushroom soup.
Stir until well blended and no soup lumps.
Cut Velveeta into small cubes and stir into the mixture.
Smooth top and cut up the butter over the top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Check after 35 to 40 minutes.
If cheese seems melted, it is done.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Mix with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Toss with salad dressing.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture alternately with the sour cream; beat well. Gently fold in egg whites.
Bake in a well greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 90 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: hot apple drink
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in bottom of percolator. Place spices in basket of percolator.
Heat mixture until it comes to a full perk.
Perk for 3 minutes.
Keep hot or warm until served.

title: tuna tumbales
directions: Lightly brown tuna and onion in oil.
Add yolks, bread, lemon juice, parsley and seasonings.
Fold egg whites in and turn into greased custard cups.
Bake in pan of water at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm in center.
Top with white sauce.
Serves 4.

title: sourdough starter(servings:  3 cups)
directions: In a 2-quart plastic pitcher with strainer in lid or a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat with a wooden or plastic spoon.
Fermentation will dissolve small lumps.
Cover pitcher with lid, turning strainer in lid to pouring lip.
Cover bowl with a cloth.
Set in a warm place, free from drafts.
Let stand 1 to 2 days, stirring occasionally.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; crumble and drain. Cut bread into cubes and put in 9 x 13 baking dish.

Sprinkle sausage over bread; put cheese on top of this. Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard; pour this over bread, sausage and cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add Jell-O mixture and strawberries to cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until done, about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for a few minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Set aside to cool. Cream sugar, butter and eggs and add to flour and nuts.
Add cooled date mixture to batter and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan or tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch buttered pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: beef and cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion.
Remove from heat and drain.
In large bowl combine beef, onion, spaghetti sauce, macaroni, cheese and spices.
Bake covered 20 minutes or until bubbly.
You can sprinkle with more cheese and bake another 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: breakfast ambrosia
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl; toss to mix well.
Makes 4 cups.
Keep for 5 days in refrigerator.
Can add 1 cup chopped nuts and maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: potato pudding
directions: Cook potatoes and mash while still warm.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Put mixture into well-greased, heat resistant 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serve and enjoy!

title: creamy peach salad
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup.
Soften cream cheese.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add softened cream cheese and beat with rotary beater.
Add peaches, cut in pieces, lemon juice and peach syrup.
Pour into square Pyrex dish (or other container) that has been greased with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired. Refrigerate until set firmly.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: texas cake
directions: Spoon cherries over the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Spread pineapple over cherry pie filling. Sift cake mix over pineapple. Melt margarine and drip evenly over cake mix. Sprinkle pecans and coconut on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May have to put foil over top to keep coconut from burning after cake cooks 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of the cracker crumbs with melted butter or margarine. Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix vegetables, cheese, onion, celery and mayo in a bowl.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Put remainder of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add chopped onions.
Cook until clear.
Add 2 boxes chopped broccoli and stir.
Add mushroom soup.
Simmer until broccoli is tender.
Add Cheez Whiz; mix well. Add cooked rice; stir.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Stir cider, sugar, salt and pepper into bacon drippings.
Tear lettuce into bite-size bits.
Pour warm dressing over lettuce and onion slices.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In sauce pan melt peanut butter and butter. In large bowl combine powdered sugar and cereal then mix the peanut butter mixture into it. Blend with hands forming into 1/2 inch balls. Chill until firm about 1 hour. Melt chocolate pieces in double boiler. Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate mix to coat. Place on wax paper until cool.

title: dried beef canapes
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Add onion to cheese. Spread on slices of beef.
Roll up.
Chill.
Cut into thirds. Spear with toothpicks.
May add horseradish.

title: fudge pie
directions: In a medium mixing bow combine butter, sugar, eggs, cocoa, flour, and vanilla.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.
Let cool, cut and serve.

title: smokey's swedish tea ring cake
directions: Mix ingredients for 6 minutes with mixer.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat the oleo, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add the bananas and water; mix.
Add the dry ingredients.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with foil.
Chop peanuts.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler and pour into a bowl.
Melt peanut butter chips in double boiler.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat melted peanut butter chips into cream cheese.
Press half the fudge into bottom of pan.
Cover remaining mixture to prevent drying out.
Spread melted chocolate over fudge in pan.
Freeze 5 minutes to set quickly.
Press remaining fudge over chocolate.
When set, cut into small squares.

title: turkey vegetable kebabs
directions: Preheat broiler.
In blender, combine garlic, mustard, lemon juice and oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Cut turkey into 1 1/2-inch cubes. Place in bowl with mustard mixture for about 10 minutes.

title: easy meatloaf dinner
directions: Mold ground chuck into a loaf.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix, then pat in.
Pour 2 cans cream of mushroom soup over the top of the loaf.
Surround with medium, thick-sliced potatoes.
Seal in tin foil and bake at 350 degrees for approx. 2 hours.

title: jo's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute
onions in butter.
Stir	in
flour.
Add
water. Cook over low heat
until thickens.
Blend in cheese.
Combine this sauce with broccoli and eggs.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with
cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dessert fruit pizza
directions: Spray large pizza pan or cookie sheet with cooking spray (or use nonstick pan).
With very sharp knife, slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Starting at edge, line cookie slices around pan, overlapping slightly to make a pretty scalloped crust.
Continue filling pan with slices to cover.
Bake in a 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes, until cookies are set, but not brown.
Remove from oven. Set aside.
Lower oven heat to 325°.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook ring macaroni.
Mix macaroni, dressing and drained fruit. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add the Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and pepper until onion is transparent.
Add ground chuck, garlic and oregano; brown.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce and paste, then add salt.
Cook over low heat, 2 1/2 to 3 hours, add the wine and cook 15 more minutes.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top.

title: queen elizabeth's cake (1954)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour water over the dates and baking soda.
Let stand.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla. Add the flour, baking powder and salt, that have been mixed together.
Add to the date mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake 35 minutes.
Cool.
Combine brown sugar, cream and butter in a small pan.
Boil for 3 minutes and spread over cake.
Sprinkle with additional nuts and coconut.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Slowly stir
in
milk. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until
thick
enough
to
mound
when dropped from a spoon.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. Stir
a	little hot mixture into egg yolks, then stir into rest of hot mixture. Cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly. Remove from
double boiler. Stir in vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut. Cool
at room temperature.
Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites.
Add
sugar, one
tablespoon
at a time, beating well after
each
addition. Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread on top of
pie. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut. Bake at 425° for 5 minutes until meringue is lightly browned. Cool.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 dashes of lemon pepper. Let chill for 1 hour.
Serve over lettuce.

title: meat balls
directions: Saute onion in two tablespoons of butter until soft.
Add to bread crumbs.
Add beef, seasoniong and egg.
Form into one inch balls, and bake in oven on broiler rack at 400° until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: tomato jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart glass microwave bowl.
Cook in microwave for 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.
After finished, mix well with mixer.
Pour in serving bowl.

title: marinated onions
directions: Soak sliced onions in cold, salty water (add ice cubes) for one hour or longer; drain off most of water.
Add vinegar and sugar; stir well.
Keep covered with additional ice cubes or in covered container in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin roll filling
directions: Mix together until light and smooth.
Unroll cooled cake; spread filling over cake.
Reroll cake and filling together, pulling up on end of towel to help roll cake.
Wrap in clear wrap or wax paper and chill.
Slice to serve.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, butter, sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Add egg yolks. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: one dish chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing, boiling water and margarine.
Spoon stuffing across center of 3-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on side of stuffing.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Add to pudding mixture, topping with balance of Cool Whip.

title: ground beef gumbo
directions: Cook beef, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in heavy Dutch oven until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour. Remove bay leaves. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts gumbo.

title: cheesy ham and corn pie
directions: Saute onion and red and green pepper in butter until soft (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and milk in large bowl until blended.
Add onion-pepper mixture, ham, corn, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; combine thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: braised pork tenderloins
directions: Cut tenderloins into 1-inch steak-like pieces.
Place soy sauce, water, sugar and wine into a bowl; stir well.
Drop in tenderloins, set into refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir once or twice during this time.

title: easy lasagna(no precooking of pasta)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, seasoning and sugar.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of uncooked lasagna pieces, 1 cup Ricotta and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce and remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Can be precooked 1/2 of time, frozen to be finished cooking and used later.

title: moes' meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef.
Add beef; mix thoroughly. Bake in loaf pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp and lobster in white wine
directions: In large kettle bring 2 1/2-quarts water to boil.
Add lobster and reduce heat.
Simmer 8 minutes.
Lift out and cool.
Return water to boil.
Add shrimp and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Remove meat from lobster shells, cut into bite-size.
Set aside.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and scrape squash.
Slice into buttered baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in bacon drippings and top with sliced onion.
Cover and bake in medium oven at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake until squash is tender and juice has cooked out.

title: crustless coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, in blender.
Process for 5 minutes (a hand mixer may be used).
Stir in coconut.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350° or until set.
Pie will puff and then fall slightly.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Set your oven to 350°.	Cook wild rice and add 1 can of cream of	mushroom,
can of celery and 1 can of water;
mix together. Place
in	buttered
x 13-inch casserole.
Layer chicken on top
of rice mixture and sprinkle onion mix on top of chicken. Bake for 2 hours or until done.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: stuffaronis
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water 15 minutes; drain.
Add a bit of oil to keep from sticking.
Combine garlic, onion and meats and saute in oil 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Combine crumbs, spinach, cheese and egg and add to meat mixture.

title: perch new orleans
directions: In a skillet, saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Add broth, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Place pickling spice in a small piece of cheesecloth and tie closed.
Add to sauce and simmer for 45 minutes.
In a separate skillet, flour and brown fish.
Remove the pickling spice; add the fish.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: turkey burgers with sage and onion
directions: Preheat the broiler; set rack 6 inches from heat.
Combine all ingredients.
Form 4 patties.
Broil 5 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.
Serves 4.

title: eve bulen's lemon meringue pie
directions: Meringue Crust:
Grease large pie pan.
Beat egg whites with sugar; add cream of tartar after frothy.
Bake 20 minutes at 275°, then turn oven to 300° for 40 minutes.
Let cool in oven.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together well all ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
(Garnish with candied cherry halves, if desired.)
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from sheet immediately. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Mix ingredients in order listed.
To preserve color and freshness until serving, put avocado seed down in dip and cover until ready to use.
Serve with large, dip size Fritos.

title: macaroons (coconut)
directions: Combine coconut, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon, 1-inch apart, onto well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Remove at once from pan.
Makes about 30.

title: amish cake
directions: Mix and bake in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan 35 minutes at 370°.

title: easy salmon patties
directions: In medium bowl, combine salmon and its liquid (picking out large bones) with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into patties or balls.
Fry in Crisco shortening 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook celery, onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon butter in double boiler for 5 minutes.
Add pimento and chicken.
Make white sauce with 5 tablespoons butter, flour and milk.
Add soup and mushrooms; mix well.
Pour into a shallow baking dish.
Cover with mixed cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
In one hole put 1 teaspoon vanilla, in another put 1 tablespoon vinegar and in another put 6 tablespoons of melted oleo. Add 1 cup water and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country cornish pastries
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into 1/4-inch slices.
In a saucepan, heat the bacon grease and slightly saute onion.
Add the sliced potatoes and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until the potatoes are fork-tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain any remaining water and add the corned beef.
Stir well.
Slightly mash some of the potatoes as you stir.
Add the salt and pepper.
Let the mixture cool to room temperature.
Roll the pie crust into individual 8 to 9-inch circles.
Place 1 cup of the meat and potato mixture on half of each circle.
Fold over and press the edges to seal.
Beat together the egg and milk and brush over the pastries.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until light brown.
These are good served at room temperature.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine the ground beef, rice, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Form small balls and brown in skillet. Drain excess fat and transfer to a casserole. Pour tomato juice over meat balls; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili rellenos won tons(appetizers)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except won ton skins together and blend well.
Fill won ton skins with 1/2 teaspoon of mixture. (Place mixture in center of skin, moisten edges and seal.)
Filled skins are then dropped into 6 inches of oil that has been heated for deep frying.
They take around 30 to 45 seconds in oil to become crispy and golden.
Remove with slotted spoon to paper towels and cool.
To freeze, place on foil-lined cookie sheet and freeze until hard.
Store in box or plastic bag.
Preheat oven to 325° and reheat until hot.

title: deluxe scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in buttered pan.
Bake until golden brown on top at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Put in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Mix together cream and milk and pour over sugar and flour. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: tuna and cheese biscuit casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery seed in margarine.
Add flour and mix well, then combine gradually with milk.
Stir in soup and tuna. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make biscuit dough according to Bisquick directions.
Cover the dough with cheese spread.
Roll the dough and slice 1 1/4-inches thick.
Arrange on top of tuna mixture and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are cooked underneath (lift to see).
If too brown, reduce heat.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: gail's banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar with a hand mixer.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add orange juice and bananas; mix well.
Mix in all dry ingredients until just moist.
Pour into a greased loaf or 9 x 9-inch square or 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Check for doneness and bake longer or remove if knife comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 1 hour and remove.

title: festival sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan, boil sweet potatoes in their skins 20 to 30 minutes or until tender. Peel and put through ricer or mash. Season with salt and 1/4 cup brown sugar or to taste. Form into balls, using an ice cream scoop, and place amount on top of each slice of pineapple. Heat remaining brown sugar and liquid together until sugar is dissolved; pour over potatoes and pineapple. Bake 30 minutes, basting often with syrup in pan. Serves 6.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Melt
butter
in
a
bread pan.
Add apple pie filling. Mix sugar,
flour, egg and milk.
Mixture has to be relatively thin. Pour over apples and bake at 350°.

title: super easy pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in thin strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
While you prepare vegetables, heat oil in large frying pan; add beef and toss over high heat until brown.
Cover; simmer 30 to 40 minutes, until tender, over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables (not tomatoes).
Toss until tender (10 minutes).
Mix cornstarch with cold water; add to meat and vegetable mixture.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes until they are hot clear through. Serve over white rice.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until dissolved.
Add half the flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough that does not stick to sides of bowl.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and allow to rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Cover and let rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Let rise until doubled, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.

title: hamburger veg. soup
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain off excess grease. Add everything but canned vegetables and simmer for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.
Add canned vegetables and cook for about 5 minutes more.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown the beef and onion together; drain.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put layer of cabbage and half of the beef mixture.
Add another layer of cabbage and the remainder of the beef.
Sprinkle a little cabbage on top and pour the undiluted tomato soup on top.
Cover with foil and bake in oven for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and Crisco in	large bowl and mix until crumbly.
A pastry blender is helpful.
In	a
small
bowl, mix egg, water and vinegar.
Add to
flour
mix
and
combine until moistened.	Divide dough into 5 to	6
portions.
Wrap each one in plastic and chill.	Each portion will make one 9-inch crust. You can thaw, freeze, refreeze, re-roll
and
it won't hurt its quality.
How nice to reach into the
freezer
and find it, but thaw it in the fridge before rolling.

title: open-faced peach pie
directions: Lay peaches in pie crust, cut side up. Mix salt, flour and sugar. Cut in margarine. Add boiling water and flavoring. Pour over peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce as you would for meat loaf until you can roll the mixture into balls.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place into lightly greased 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. (Cover pan lightly with foil to prevent splattering.)
Drain meatballs on paper towel.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: perfect popovers
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, beat eggs slightly with a fork or whisk.
Stir in milk and cooking oil.
Add flour and salt.
With whisk, beat egg-flour mixture until smooth.
(Batter will be thin). Transfer into six-ounce custard cups that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 40 minutes in a 400° oven.
Do not open oven door while baking.
When done, prick with a fork, this prevents popovers from getting soggy.
Shut oven off and let popovers stay in oven a further 5 to 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil, dull side up.
Break each cracker in half and fill pan.

title: mexican beef
directions: Spread meat with mixture of garlic, pepper, salt, chili powder and mustard.
Cut into 1/2-inch wide strip.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Add onions, bouillon cube and tomatoes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put 1 box frozen strawberries in bottom of bowl.
Put one layer of baked cake on top.
Punch holes in layer with wooden spoon, then slice 2 1/2 bananas.
Add 1 package vanilla pudding (mix according to directions).
Pour on top of bananas, then add last cake layer.
Spread can of pineapple (juice and all); layer last box strawberries on top.
Add rest of bananas and second pack of mixed pudding.
Add Cool Whip, coconut and pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves up to 25.
Great for cookouts.

title: granola
directions: Combine dry ingredients in very large bowl.
Heat remaining ingredients (not boil).
Pour wet ingredients over dry ingredients to coat evenly.
Grease 4 cookie sheets.
Spread mixture on sheets and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and store in sealed container.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and butter in a small deep saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat to 300° or hard crack stage. Add pecans and cook to 310°.
Stir in soda, pour into lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let stand until cold and break into pieces.

title: ceci insalata(chickpea salad)
directions: Mix peas, celery, onion, pepper and tomato in a bowl.
Shake or stir dressing (remaining ingredients) and pour over salad. Marinate several hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: french fried cream cheese and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread cream cheese on one slice of bread.
Spread jelly on second slice of bread.
Put sandwich together.
Heat oil or oleo in frying pan.
Fry sandwich on both sides until lightly browned. Put on plate; sprinkle with confectioners sugar and enjoy!

title: scratch chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix lemon jello and boiling water together; cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Add jello mixture and mix well.
Chill until thickened.

title: animals in dirt
directions: Using small individual bowls, break up 2 graham crackers.
Add some miniature marshmallows and pour some chocolate pudding over top.
Then stick some animal crackers into the pudding.
Be sure to leave their heads sticking out so you have animals in the dirt!

title: kahlua mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks and 2 tablespoons Kahlua in the top of a double boiler.
Beat in 1/4 cup sugar; beat until slightly thickened and color lightens.
Place pan over boiling water.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Set top of double boiler in a bowl of cold water.
beat until mixture is thick, 3 to 4 minutes. Melt chocolate and butter together.
Stir in remaining 2 tablespoons Kahlua.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add remaining sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Beat whipping cream until stiff. Fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon mousse into parfait glasses or dessert cups. Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add water and then dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Turn into 3 (8-inch) greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with coconut frosting.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies, then mix butter with cookies and set aside. Blend 10 ounces of Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese (cream cheese needs to be soft).
Set this aside also.
Blend chocolate pudding with milk, then add remaining 6 ounces of Cool Whip.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but not mushy.
Peel and shred in large flat casserole.
Cool potatoes well before shredding.
I usually do potatoes the day before and let cool in refrigerator overnight.
Heat together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix together cream cheese, lemon juice, garlic salt, olives and jalapeno peppers.
Place a large spoonful on top of each tortilla and spread it out.
Layer meats on top of mixture*.
Roll and wrap in plastic bag or wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Cut and serve.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O together.
Add oil; blend well.
Add sugar and water; blend well.
Pour into 3 layer pans or 1 large cake pan.
Bake at 350° until cake does not stick to toothpick.

title: mamaw's chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, Nestle Quik, 1 1/4 cups milk and 2 egg yolks together.
Blend cornstarch with remaining 1/4 cup milk until smooth, then add to saucepan.
As mixture is heating, add Pet milk.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken, stirring continuously.
Once mixture is thick, spoon in 1 teaspoon butter and mix well.
Immediately pour into baked pie shell and cool 2 hours before serving.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt together. Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and molasses to creamed mixture, mixing well. Add dry ingredients alternately with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Drop by heaping spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in moderate oven, 350° to 375°, for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Fry cut dried beef in butter until edges curl, approximately 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper.
Sprinkle flour over top of beef; stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.

title: grandma roper's pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine ingredients.
Pour ingredients into pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Invert pan and serve.

title: chicken italian style
directions: Add salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese to chicken.
Mix egg and 1 tablespoon oil together.
Dip chicken into egg, then flour and bread crumbs.
Put into pan with oil and brown.
Add mushrooms and sauce and lemon (optional).
Before serving, add Mozzarella cheese.

title: texas trash
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt together butter, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and oregano.
In a plastic bag, mix all other ingredients plus melted (but cooled slightly) butter mixture.
Toss gently until mixture is evenly coated.
Place in a large baking dish and bake for 1 hour, stirring mixture every 15 minutes.
Should be dry, loose and lightly browned.

title: turtle bars(german caramel bars)
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup milk in double boiler; keep warm. Mix dry cake mix, 1/3 cup milk, butter and nuts. Put 1/2 of the batter in a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 325° for 6 minutes. Remove and put chocolate chips on bars. Pour caramels over chips. Then spread remaining batter on the caramel. Bake 15 to 20 minutes more. Let cool 30 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Mix together butter, honey, mustard and curry powder.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture; place in 9x12 inch pan (line with aluminum foil for easy clean up).
Pour remaining sauce over chicken and bake 1 hour at 375°.
The honey burns easily so watch it and reduce temperature if necessary.
If you like more sauce, double recipe.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, salt, eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
Cover and set away from draft to raise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Divide and knead on floured board.
Place in well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Cover and let rise to top of pan.
Bake 35 minutes. Wrap in foil.
Bread freezes well.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make cake according to instructions on box, adding 1 cup coconut to batter.
Bake according to instructions on box.
While cake is still hot, poke holes with meat fork or ice pick over entire top of cake until covered with holes.
Immediately pour cream of coconut over top of cake, then pour crushed pineapple over top of cake.
When cake is cool, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: turkey chile relleno casserole
directions: Brown sausage until crumbled and well done. Add onion and cook until soft.
Add salsa and simmer until mixture thickens. Beat milk, egg, flour, salt and m.s.g. until fluffy.
Add cheese. Layer chilies, sausage mixture, egg and cheese mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Repeat layers ending with egg and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dolmitas(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Saute onion slowly in nonstick pan until soft, adding stock, if necessary to prevent sticking or burning. Saute veal with garlic and herbs until browned. Add rice, salt and pepper. Cook gently for 5 minutes. Add additional 1/4 cup veal or chicken stock.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour and vanilla; beat well. Fold in pecans.
Pour into greased 10 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss all ingredients together.
Keep refrigerated for best results.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Stir-fry onion, celery and cabbage in oil in skillet for 1 minute.
Add broth and soy sauce.
Cook over high heat until cabbage is tender-crisp, stirring constantly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Wash, peel and core apples.
Prepare slices 1/2-inch wide and place in 1 gallon water containing 1 level teaspoon ascorbic acid or 6 tablets (500 milligrams Vitamin C) to prevent browning.

title: ripple cake
directions: Crumble pound cake in large casserole dish.
Add 1 layer of bananas.
Cover with whipped cream.
Pour on pineapple chunks and another layer of whipped cream.
Put on layer of blueberries and one layer of strawberries.
Cover well with whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Blend together until moist.
Press in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: clam or shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on crackers and eat!!!

title: peppy bean dip
directions: Blend together the refried beans, sour cream and finely chopped jalapeno peppers.
Mix well.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese and sliced green onion.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: nasa grits
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan and crumble.
Add onion, bell pepper and ham in bacon drippings.
Add salt and pepper, tomatoes, cooked grits and egg.
Mix and bake in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Better to marinate overnight before cooking.)

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
In large bowl, cream the butter. Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the wafer crumbs and milk alternately.
Add coconut; fold in pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand in pan a few minutes before turning out.
Better served the day after baking.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream the shortenings and 1 1/2 cups of sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Sift together the next 4 ingredients; mix well with the first mixture.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Then gradually mix in the flour, oats, chips and pecans.
Use teaspoon to shape cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 100.

title: festive salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and pineapple and cook until thickens. Add jello; mix well.
Add ice cubes and chill.
Add whipping cream after beating until stiff.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Chill!

title: beef roast in the coals
directions: Prepare fire so that coals are hot.
Cover entire surface of meat with mustard.
Pat salt into mustard until it won't hold any more.
Insert meat thermometer.
Place meat directly on coals; rake coals around meat.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Turn over and cook 45 minutes (140° rare, 160° medium and 170° well done). Remove meat from coals.
Remove black crust which formed.
To serve, across the grain.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Bake brownies in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over brownies.
Melt peanut butter and chips over low heat (use double boiler).
Stir to mix.
Stir in Rice Krispies and put over marshmallow layer.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix in large bowl.

title: italian spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, chili powder, garlic salt, hamburger meat, savory salt and Italian spice.
Cook at high temperature while mashing the meat and ingredients with a fork. When hamburger is cooked through, then add tomato sauce, water, vinegar, salt and pepper and olives.
Cook at high temperature for 10 minutes, then over medium-low flame for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook spaghetti for approximately 20 or 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain water off and cover the spaghetti with meat sauce in a large platter.
Sprinkle generously with your favorite cheese (optional).

title: catherine's spaghetti with clams
directions: Note:
Brand name and fresh ingredients produce excellent results.
Great gourmet meal for unexpected guests.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Lightly cook broccoli. Add the other ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat (quickly) in
oil,
then
add
mushrooms and onion. Cook until onion is
tender, about 3 minutes.
Add the broth, Worcestershire, paprika and
tomato
paste and bring to boil. Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes and stir in sour cream.

title: white chili
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, 1 teaspoon lemon pepper and cumin seed. Bring to a boil. Add chicken breast halves. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is "fork tender". Remove chicken from bones and cut into 1-inch pieces. Return chicken to saucepan. Spray medium skillet with cooking spray.
Heat oven to medium heat.
Add 1 minced garlic clove, cook 1 minute and remove from pan. Add to chicken. Add onions to skillet; cook until tender.
Add onions, corn, chilies, ground cumin and lime juice to chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil. Add beans and cook until thoroughly heated through.

title: meatball-mushroom-broccoli stew
directions: In a large frypan, saute mushrooms in butter until golden. Add broth and bring to a boil.
Combine beef, water, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Shape in walnut size meatballs and drop into simmering broth; simmer 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower nuts, onion and bacon. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over broccoli mixture.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over meat in baking pan or Dutch oven.
Cover.
Bake 6 hours at 300°.
When cool, remove any bone or fat.
Makes great sandwiches.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries into 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Pour in crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle with box of cake mix.
Dot with butter, don't stir.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or 2 round pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Beat all ingredients, except frosting, in large mixing bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean:
rectangular pan, 60 to 65 minutes or layer pans 50 to 55 minutes.

title: tempura batter(for shrimp or vegetables)
directions: Measure flour in a bowl and add COLD water.
Stir slightly until flour is lumpy (do not overmix!).
Add a cold egg and stir lightly - not too much!
Batter must be cold at all times!
Too much mixing, or if the batter becomes warm will make the batter doughy.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: memow's pecan pie
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except pecans.
Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: pear lime jello
directions: Drain pears, saving the juice. Add water to pear juice to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil. Add lime Jell-O and mix for 2 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together;
bring to boil and boil for 7 minutes.
Pour this over 1 1/2 cups peanut butter and 12 ounces Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until thick and cooled.
Pour into a
9-inch
greased
pan.
Chill.
Cut into desired size.
Will keep a month.
Makes 5 pounds.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rosemary punch
directions: Heat 1 cup pineapple juice until boiling; add rosemary and steep 5 to 8 minutes.
Dissolve sugar and salt in juice, then strain into pitcher containing the remaining pineapple juice, lemon juice and water.
Chill.
Before serving, add the ginger ale and float lemon slices and mint leaves.
Punch can be served hot.

title: chicken-mushroom casserole
directions: Mix milk, mushroom soup, 1/2 can mushrooms (drained) and 1/2 package dry onion soup mix.
Pour out 1/2 cup.
Add rice to remaining mixture.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: bacon onion appetizer
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Unroll crescent rolls and separate into 8 rectangles; firmly press diagonal perforations to seal.
Spread butter mixture evenly over dough.
Roll up each rectangle beginning with short side; pinch seam to seal.
Cut into 4 slices.
Place pinwheels on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Roll the biscuit pieces in the sugar and drop into a greased Bundt pan.
Mix remaining sugars, milk and margarine. Bring to a boil and pour over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swordfish jardiniere
directions: In small saucepan, combine butter, lemon juice, mustard and pepper; heat thoroughly over low heat.
Brush large sheet of heavy-duty foil with butter mixture; arrange steaks in center of foil.
Pour remaining butter mixture over steaks.
Top with carrots, dill and parsley.
Bring long sides of foil together; double fold sides and end of foil.
Grill over medium-low heat with grill top closed, 10 to 12 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Combine all and heat to simmering.
Don't boil.
Strain and serve.
Serves a large group.

title: best chicken salad
directions: Brush chicken breasts with melted butter, salt and pepper, then wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 350°
an hour or until done.
Skin, remove bones and cut into chunks the cooked chicken.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake and pudding as directed on packages.
In large punch bowl, place one layer of cake and top with 1/2 of the strawberries, 1/2 pineapple, 2 sliced bananas and 1/2 pudding, then start over with next layer of cake and repeat steps.
Then top off with Cool Whip.

title: easy kolackies
directions: Beat margarine and cream cheese together until well blended. Stir in flour.
Roll out mixture on floured surface to about 1/8-inch in thickness.
Cut out with small glass or cookie cutter. Place on baking sheet.
Top each one with a small amount of pie filling in center.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Lightly sift with powdered sugar.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Peel and core tomatoes.
Put through a blender.
Put onions and pepper through blender.
Boil for 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients with boiling mixture; boil until thick as you like, 1 to 2 hours.
Pour into pint jars.
Heat lids and seal jars.

title: zucchini a l'orange
directions: Wash squash; cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Saute in butter, turning once, until barely tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add juice; stir gently and heat until hot.
Garnish with orange rind, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butterscotch toll house morsels
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and hot water.
Add flour, mixed with soda, chopped nuts and oats.
Add vanilla and butterscotch chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Roll chops in flour, salt and pepper mix. Fry in a deep skillet until done; drain off grease. Cover with water and cover. Cook slowly for 30 minutes, adding more water, if needed. This makes a great gravy. Serve hot.

title: royal french dressing
directions: Place
all ingredients in blender and blend.
This will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Grease well a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well and pour into pan. If desired, sprinkle unseasoned bread crumbs on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 8 minutes and then drain.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and marinate overnight in the following sauce.

title: peppered tenderloin roast with burgundy gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In cup, mix pepper, olive oil and salt.
Rub mixture all over meat.
Place tenderloin on rack in large roasting pan.
Roast tenderloin 50 minutes or until meat thermometer reaches 140° or to desired doneness.

title: corn flake candy
directions: In large heavy boiler, add sugar, syrup and peanut butter. Let come to a boil and stir until all is dissolved.
Take boiler off heat and stir in cornflakes until it is all mixed well.
Then pour it in a buttered square pan or dish.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix the brown sugar and melted butter until crumbly.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Mix the milk, eggs, sugar, flour and salt and pour over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, crumble beef.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cover and microwave at High 6 minutes.
Drain meat well.
To cook meat mixture, add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes until hot.
To serve, spoon into buns.

title: paul's homestyle ice cream
directions: Pour milk into ice maker to line.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla, whipping cream, condensed milk and salt.
Blend well and wait until mixture sets.
Makes 5 quarts.
Enjoy!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook potatoes as directed.
Brown sausage and drain well. Layer potatoes, mushrooms, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs and pour over mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Will serve 12 to 15 people.

title: water gate salad
directions: Mix in one large container. Refrigerate over night.

title: vegetarian quiche
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt.
