Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of mixture; toss with a fork.
Push to side of the bowl. Repeat until all is moistened.
Form into a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough from center to edge, forming a 12-inch circle.
Fit into a 9-inch pie pastry.
Trim pastry to 1/2-inch beyond edge of pie plate.
Do not prick pastry.

title: spaghetti
directions: Put salt in bottom of frying pan.
Cook beef, onion and green pepper until beef is brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and spices.
Let sauce simmer while cooking spaghetti noodles by package directions until tender.

title: stuffed jalapenos, fried in beer batter
directions: In
a
small
saucepan,
brown ground beef, stirring to crumble real small.
Add onion, seasonings and water; bring to a boil.
Cover; lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and
stir
in rice and cheese; mix well.
Leave stems on peppers and make a small slit at top of pepper and down side. Remove seeds and stuff with rice mixture.
Dip in beer batter and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Place 3/4 of mixture in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Place chicken pieces on top of stuffing.
Mix together sour cream, soup and 1 cup of chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top. Pour remaining chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and lemon juice in bowl.
Mix with wire whisk until well blended.
Serve with fruit dippers.

title: urban-rural mixer
directions: Marinate chicken halves for 2 hours or more in marinade of vinegar and oil.
Remove and sprinkle evenly with poultry seasoning, paprika, salt and pepper.
Broil on outdoor grill. Baste with marinade while cooking.
Time to cook depends on size of chicken.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let bread thaw and rise according to package directions.
In a medium size skillet, brown sausage, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms; drain the liquid.
Roll bread dough flat on floured surface with floured rolling pin.
Place on a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread half the sausage mixture down center of dough.
Sprinkle half the cheeses over mixture; repeat.
Fold dough over and tuck in ends.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 30 minutes.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine and beat extra long.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine avocados, tomatoes, salad dressing, onion and salt. Mix well; chill.
Place in individual bowls.
Serve on plates. Sprinkle with bacon garnished with tomato wedges and tortilla chips.
Serve as a first course or luncheon, or serve ungarnished as a dip.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: cajun sausage with rice
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and wine.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cut up sausage, cayenne pepper and salt to taste.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
Mix together and serve.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers; cook in boiling salted water about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Brown beef and cook onion in butter until tender; stir in soup and remaining ingredients. Spoon meat mixture into peppers; place in casserole dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
(Makes 4 servings.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Saute onions in margarine and mix with squash.
Add bread crumbs, eggs, seasonings and cheese.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Skin chicken.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons of oil until tender.
Place chicken in oblong pan.
Top with onion and bell pepper.
Mix cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups with water.
Spread over chicken and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Turn chicken over in pan while it's cooking.
Use own judgement as to when to do this.
Fix instant rice as directed on box.
Spread gravy over rice.
Eat and enjoy.

title: strawberry-pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for exactly 8 minutes.
Set aside.
Beat sugar into cream cheese and stir in Cool Whip. Spread on cooled pretzel mix.
Dissolve strawberry Jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and mix.
Let stand until beginning to gel.
Pour over cream mixture and refrigerate.

title: goody butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
(This will be very stiff.)
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and egg together and put on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Wash beef steak; cut into four pieces.
Put 1 tablespoon of cooking oil in pan.
When heated, brown meat on both sides, then cut onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add salt and pepper and then add to meat in pan.
If you want lots of gravy, you can add one tablespoon of flour to a cup of water.
Let simmer for 25 minutes. Serves 4 or more.

title: chicken in its own juices
directions: Skin and cut chickens in small pieces.
Fry the chicken pieces in oil; fry until golden brown.
Add the tomatoes with garlic after they've been blended together.
Then add the fruits (cut into pieces), raisins, almonds, Jerez wine, vinegar, sugar and salt. Finally, add the water and leave mixture on stove top (low) until cooked.

title: cheese topped zucchini halves
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Cook onion in salad oil on medium heat until tender, but not brown.
Add zucchini halves, cut side up.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour tomato sauce over zucchini.
Cover.
Cook just until tender, about 10 minutes.
Top zucchini with cheese slices.
Cover until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: crab meat delight
directions: Sauce:
Cook butter, flour and cream in double boiler; add milk and seasonings when sauce is well blended.
Removed from heat and add well beaten egg yolks.
Add layer of crumbs, 1/2 crab and 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers in well-buttered casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs and cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.
Sealegs may be used.

title: zucchini aux herbes dete(zucchini with summer herbs)
directions: Use only fresh herbs.
Rinse zucchini and pat back.
Trim ends and cut into 1/8-inch slices, about 6 cups.
Heat oil in a skillet.
When quite hot, add zucchini.
Cook over relatively high heat, shaking the skillet, tossing and turning with spatula so all sides are turned.
Add salt and pepper and remove from pan, 5 to 7 minutes.
Put butter in skillet and melt.
Return zucchini to pan and garlic and herbs.
Toss.
Serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
You can always add bananas the next day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir together pumpkin, oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for about 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain off all broth, except 2 cups.
Add cream of chicken soup and stir well.
Melt butter and crumble the bread in it.
Spray your baking dish with your favorite nonstick spray and place the chicken and broth mixture into it.
Layer the bread crumbs on top of chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until browned.

title: cream cheese pistachio dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it just starts to brown.
Cool completely.

title: fluffy fruit dip
directions: Cut up any large pieces of fruit in preserves; place in a small bowl.
Stir in sour cream and walnuts.
Add enough milk to make mixture the consistency for dipping.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve with assorted fruit and cheeses.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: devilicious party spread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, deviled ham, Worcestershire and cayenne pepper.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in green and red peppers.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or vegetables. Makes approximately 2 cups dip.

title: ginger cream cheese ball
directions: Chop dates, ginger and nuts in a food processor or mince by hand.
Add cheese; blend well.
Chill 2 hours; shape into large ball or 2 small ones.
Cover with flaked coconut.
Serve with gingersnaps.
Will serve 20.

title: easy homemade biscuits
directions: Blend together flour and shortening, add buttermilk.
Stir gently with fork until soft dough forms.
Put on floured pastry cloth and knead gently.
Pat to 1 inch thick.
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: taco pie(low-fat)
directions: Cook turkey or veal.
Mix with water and taco mix.
Cook until thick.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan or oblong casserole sprayed with Pam.
Layer all but the last 3 ingredients.
Mix last 3; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings; 4 proteins, 1 bread, 1/4
milk, 1 vegetable and 20 optional calories.

title: strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch and 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put 10 slices of bread in the pans; layer with meat and cheese.
Cover with bread. Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and onion; pour over bread.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes, or until middle appears firm.

title: some-mores
directions: Arrange thin, sweet chocolate on graham cracker, put hot toasted marshmallow on chocolate, then cover with another graham cracker.
Press two crackers together.
The hot marshmallow melts the chocolate to form a delicious dessert sandwich.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: To chicken broth add noodles, celery, onion and green pepper. Cook 30 minutes; then add Worcestershire sauce, file, mushrooms, tomato soup and pimentos.
Add chicken and mix and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 30.

title: tomato relish
directions: Pour boiling water over washed tomatoes; let stand until peel comes off easily.
Peel, core and chop.
Cook all ingredients together until thick (several hours).
Put in jars and process.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and slightly drained pineapple.
Add orange soda.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: ribbon jello
directions: You will need an 8-inch square glass pan.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Fill hot dog rolls and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add the rest.
Blend well.
Grease and flour pans well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick beans
directions: Put beans or peas in a 4-quart pan; cover with water.
Bring to a boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Turn off burner; let set for 1 hour. Pour off water.
Cover with 5 or 6 inches of water and bring to a boil.
Add seasonings, salt, chili powder, garlic, salt pork, etc. Boil on low heat for 1 hour.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: jen's brew(king ranch chicken)
directions: Boil chicken.
In skillet, saute onion and pepper until clear, then add soups (mushroom, Ro-Tel and cream of chicken).
Chop chicken; put in soup mixture.
Dip 6 or more tortillas in chicken broth.
Spray pan with Pam, then pour 1/2 of chicken mixture in pan.
Spread some cheese.
Add the tortillas that have been dipped in chicken broth to cover.
Add rest of mixture.
Add chili and garlic powder.
Add rest of cheese.
Bake for approximately 5 to 15 minutes.

title: red cabbage(german)
directions: Shred cabbage thin. Brown diced onion and apples (with peel) in large pot with bacon drippings.

Cook slowly until tender, about 10 minutes. Add cabbage, salt, sugar and vinegar. Cook over low heat until cabbage is tender. Check seasoning before serving. May be divided and put in plastic bags and frozen for future use.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Bring water and juice to a boil.
Add jello and let cool until partly congealed.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Set until firm in refrigerator.
Cream the sugar and cream cheese together; fold in sour cream.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 12 minutes.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Boil raisins well and drain.
Melt butter; add sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, raisins and nuts.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: smothered beef tips
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy roasting pan, preferably cast-iron.
Cover; bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Check after 1 hour to see if more water is needed.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: fruit walnut salad
directions: Arrange fruit on greens; garnish with walnuts.
Drizzle with yogurt dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach walnut pie
directions: Combine peaches and sugar in saucepan.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch, butter, walnuts, cinnamon and extract; let cool.
Put into a 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with top crust brushed with egg yolks.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cool and crumble cornbread in bowl.
Add all except dressing. Pour dressing over ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
This will fill a very large salad bowl.

title: skipper's linguine
directions: Cook bacon and drain 1/2 cup fat.
Cook onion and garlic in rest of drippings until tender, not brown. Add margarine.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks; combine with milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients; mix until smooth.
Stir in berries, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on hot, greased griddle.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: veal milanesse
directions: Cover veal with flour; dip in eggs and cover with bread crumbs.

Brown on both sides in oil, about 3 minutes on each side. Place in baking dish and cover all pieces with tomato sauce. Bake at 350° to 375° for 3 minutes or until sauce starts to boil. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet dream torte
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Blend in chocolate.
Beat cream until soft peaks form; gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Split cake into three layers.
Spread each layer with cream cheese mixture; stack. Frost sides with cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: holiday mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container.

title: kathy's pie
directions: Mix together Karo syrup, peanut butter and Rice Krispies. Press into pie plate.
Add ice cream, fresh fruit of choice or Nestle new toppings on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: turkey and rice quiche
directions: Combine rice, turkey, tomato, onions, green pepper, basil, salt, ground pepper, milk and eggs in 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with no stick spray.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: easy one dish chicken, sausage, vegetable bake
directions: Amount of ingredients depend on how many people will be served.
Your choice to skin chicken.
Brown chicken and sausage in olive oil for a few minutes (just to brown, not to cook).
Cut peppers into thick strips, quarter onions and potatoes (depending on size).
Place some good olive oil in roasting pan; toss in all the above ingredients.
Add lots of sliced or chopped garlic, salt and pepper.
Toss well, so all is coated with olive oil.
Roast in oven at 350° until perfect.
Do not cover roasting pan as that steams instead of roasting.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: favorite salad dressing
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and beat well, using electric mixer or egg beater.
Then gradually add oil, then remainder of vinegar, then celery seed, beating continuously until very thick.

title: pickled okra or beans
directions: Wash okra well and pack whole pods firmly into jars.
Put 1 clove garlic, 1 hot pepper and 1/2 teaspoon dill seed in each of 4 pint jars.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over okra, leaving 2-inch headspace.
Run a table knife around side of jar to remove air bubbles.
Adjust lids.
Process jar in boiling hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Pour into two well greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Do not remove cake from pans.
Punch holes in each layer.
Dissolve gelatin separately.
Pour one flavor over each layer.
Chill 4 hours.
Put layers together using Cool Whip as icing.
Do no try to ice sides.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat well the first four ingredients.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer just before serving.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in vanilla, vinegar, oil and water.
Fill cupcake tins 1/2 full with chocolate batter and top with heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Frost with white frosting.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Pour juice off beets; add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Then add sugar, vinegar, whole allspice, cloves and cinnamon.
Boil all ingredients 15 minutes; cool.
Pour over beets.

title: broccoli-woccoli salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer together for 20 minutes. Great on spareribs.

title: chicken broccoli supreme
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika and pepper.
In skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken and cook, turning 5 to 7 minutes until browned.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add mushrooms to skillet, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: mmm salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Rinse rice in warm water and drain or soak rice in 2 cups boiling salted water for 30 minutes.
Add to meat, butter and spices.
Mix well.

title: quick orange mold
directions: Blend these ingredients well.
Fold in drained pineapple. Chill overnight.

title: mystery pie
directions: Crush Ritz crackers fine.
Add finely chopped nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla; mix with crackers and nuts.
Pour into well buttered 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cook well; top with whipped cream, sweetened and flavored to taste.
Add the instant cocoa to the whipped cream.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: fresh lemon bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed except last 2.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes; check with toothpick.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and juice from fresh lemon.
Heat slowly until mixture is clear.
Pour mixture over baked bread while still hot.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Remove bread from pan onto rack to cool.

title: pickle slices
directions: Combine all ingredients except zucchini, squash or cucumbers in your blender and let it run until everything has become a thin puree.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix well.
Stir until crackers are coated.

title: chicken wings with spanish rice
directions: Drain wings.
Pat dry.
Heat the oil over moderate heat until hot, but not smoking.
Add onion and garlic; cook until soft and slightly browned, stirring constantly.
Remove onion from skillet and set aside.
Brown wings lightly, remove from pan and set aside. Add rice, salt, pepper, tomatoes and chicken stock.
Dissolve saffron in 1 tablespoon hot water; add to chicken.
Cover and simmer until rice and chicken are tender.
Add peas and pimentos, stir gently into rice.
Reheat and serve.
Enjoy.

title: gay's favorite strawberry cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients; add milk, flour, baking powder, almond extract and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer. Grease 2 (7-inch) cake pans.
Flour inside.
Whip egg whites with sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Divide batter into cake pan; cover with whipped egg whites to form peaks.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over both layers.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven until tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Assemble cake. Place first layer with meringue on bottom.
Put strawberries (frozen) and juice in center with whipped cream.
Add upper layer with meringue up.
Put rest of cream over cake.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: pork chops teriyaki
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine everything but pork chops. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Dip each chop into sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes, until done.
Pass sauce separately.
Serves 5 or more.

title: hot tuna puffs
directions: Drain tuna and flake finely.
Mix with mayonnaise, catsup, vinegar, salt, cayenne and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon mixture on the toast rounds.
Place on a cookie sheet in a preheated boiler, about 3 to 4-inches from heat, for 1 to 2 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Garnish each with a tiny parsley sprig.
Makes about 24 canapes.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Place all ingredients except oil in a blender and blend until smooth.
Place oil in a nonstick pan.
Heat until hot.
Drop batter by tablespoons onto griddle.
Brown on both sides.
Serve with blueberry sauce.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Cream margarine, add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time to sugar and margarine.
Alternate flour and milk until all is added to sugar mixture.
Add flavoring last.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan and line bottom with wax paper.
Pour batter in pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until done.
Remove from oven, let cool about 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: easy stromboli
directions: *Can use any combination.

title: spice hot tea
directions: Combine cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, lemon peel, orange peel and water in saucepan.
Mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tea bags.
Steep until of desired strength.
Remove the bags, fruit peels and whole spices.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and milk.
Sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, ginger and cloves together; stir into pumpkin mixture.
Beat 1 minute with electric beater.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin spice bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in flour and baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Place oil in pan.
Cook chicken, carrots and onions together over low heat.
When chicken is cooked, pour in remaining ingredients, except precooked eggs.
Cook for 5 minutes over low heat.
Pour cooked mixture into precooked eggs.

title: sausage breakfast bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: chipped beef and chicken breast
directions: Line greased casserole with chipped beef.
Put in chicken breasts and top each breast with bacon.
Mix sour cream and soup. Top with soup mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 40 minutes (at least). Serves 5.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend cheese and butter together until smooth and light. Combine dry ingredients; add to cheese.
Blend until smooth. Force mixture through a cookie press, using star plate.
Make long ropes of dough on cookie sheets.
Cut into 2-inch long pieces. Bake at 350° until just begin to brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: burp bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add 2 eggs and the 3 mashed bananas.
Sift and add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla last.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes in greased and floured loaf pan.

title: jello dixie lollipops(for kids)
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Let stand to cool for 15 minutes.
Pour into 4 (5-ounce) Dixie kitchen cups.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Carefully pull off the paper cup.
Have Mom use a knife to cut each gelatin cup horizontally into 3 round slices.
Push a straw (cut in half) into each gelatin circle to create a jiggly lollipop.
Makes 12 lollipops.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: In small bowl, combine hot water, sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large warm bowl. Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add first mixture, beaten egg and 2 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Punch dough down and turn out onto lightly floured board.
Divide in half.
Form each half into a 12-inch long roll. Cut rolls into 12 (1-inch) pieces.
Divide pieces into thirds; shape into smooth balls.
Place 3 balls in each greased 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cup.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Mix egg and milk; brush cloverleafs.
Sprinkle rolls with seeds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix and store in Tupperware container.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour into yeast and water. Make into a ball.
Place on greased pan, grease top of bread also. Let rise about 30 minutes covered.
Bake at 425 degree for 30 minutes.
First 20 minutes on cookie sheet and last 10 minutes on bare oven rack in oven.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: In a glass jar alternate cucumbers and onion.
In medium saucepan combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil stirring until sugar is dissolved. Pour vinegar mixture atop cukes and onion.
Cool slightly.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate pickles at least 24 hours before serving. Store up to 1 month in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Cut and remove fat from chicken.
Place the chicken on top of the rice then add water and soup.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 hours.

title: peanut pie filling
directions: Blend
syrup
with pudding mix in bowl.
Add evaporated milk and egg.
Add peanuts and pour into unbaked shell.	Bake in moderate oven (375°) until pie is set, about 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers. Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle top with crushed crackers. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Add spices to skillet with bacon fat to taste; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and bacon.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix well; dip slices of apples in it.
Eat.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs, poppy seed and melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) pans with margarine. In blender, whip eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla, blending continuously.
Add milk, flour and oil.
Put pans with mix immediately in oven and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with lots of butter, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Or, fill center with any filling, meat, fruit, etc.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Melt butter in a pan.
Pour butter into the milk and egg mixture.
Add muffin mix.
Drain Mexican corn and add to other ingredients.
Mix.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Pour batter into baking pan.
Let cook until brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and butter slices in aluminum pan. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Place on grill for 20 minutes.
Remove from grill and layer with cheese slices.
Re-cover with foil and return to grill and cook an additional 10 minutes or until done.

title: diabetic fruit and nut squares
directions: Simmer water, prunes and dates for 4 minutes.
Beat eggs, vanilla and oleo.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 squares.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in oats, dates and walnuts.
Form into balls; place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool slightly before removing to cooling rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Boil white syrup and sugar in the microwave and add
1 cup peanut butter. Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Press into jellyroll pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in lard or vegetable shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Gradually add cold water until mixture can be shaped into a ball.
Chill.
Roll out as needed.
Makes enough for 4 single crust or 2 double crust pies.

title: venison sausage
directions: Mix everything together well.
Separate into 1 pound packages and freeze.
You can use this in any recipe or as you would use pork sausage.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: In large bowl, mix broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
In small bowl, mix cheese, sugar, salt and mayonnaise.
Add dressing to vegetables.
Mix well and refrigerate several hours.
Just before serving, add bacon.
Serves 20.

title: chicken breast parmesan
directions: Combine the bread crumbs, parsley, cheese, salt and pepper. Dip the chicken in the melted butter, then roll in the bread crumb mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: fried chitterlings
directions: Wash chitterlings thoroughly and cover with boiling salted water.
Add cloves and red pepper.	Cook until tender.
Drain.
Cut in pieces the size of oyster.
Dip each piece in egg beaten with water then in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot deep fat until brown. Serves 4-6.

title: ronnie's barbecue sauce
directions: In sauce pan, mix catsup and mustard before heating (to prevent mustard from curdling).
Place over low to med heat.
Add margarine and let melt.
Add onion, salt, pepper, A-1, worcestershire and liquid smoke.
Vary quantity of liquid smoke and worcestershire as you wish for flavor.
Mix in vinegar, sugar, and Karo.
Let simmer over low heat for at least 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add other ingredients and mix well. Set in refrigerator until dough is easy to roll. Roll into 3 or 4 log shaped rolls about 6-inches long. Wrap in Saran Wrap or wax paper and let stand in refrigerator until cold enough to slice thin. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix together syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs to mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Chop onion finely.
Melt butter over low heat in saucepan with onion.
Add cream cheese and whisk until smooth.
Do not keep cooking.
Remove from heat.
Add drained shrimp and stir.
Spray mold with Pam and put dip in.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Remove to a serving plate.

title: angel food pie
directions: Follow recipe on can of pumpkin except use artificial sweetener to taste and use skimmed canned milk.
Pour into glass baking dish and bake.
When cool, cut in squares (no shell).

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers until tender.
Brown ground meat in skillet with onion, salt and pepper.
Add cooked rice to meat mixture. Add tomato sauce and put in peppers.
Then cook in microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese (optional).

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter with chocolate.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch pie plate and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut in wedges and serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
This pie freezes well.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and onion; slice thinly.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Mash potatoes with potato masher.
Add 2 more cups of water to potatoes.
Add flour to milk and stir well.
Add milk and butter to potatoes.
Chop eggs fine and add to potatoes. Cook for about 5 minutes.
Serve with corn bread or crackers.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until desired spreading consistency.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Allow lemonade and orange juice to get mushy.
Stir in fruit, water and sugar.
Stir well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch container and freeze.
Cut in blocks when ready to serve.

title: one-two-three-four pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after
each
addition.
Add
vanilla
and
mix well. Sift dry
ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour
batter
into a greased tube pan. Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: Cook and stir onions and mushrooms in hot shortening until tender.
Drain on a paper towel.
In the same skillet, brown meat, adding more shortening, if necessary.
Remove from the heat. Sprinkle seasoning over the meat.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and mix with all other ingredients.
Toast and cut muffins in 1/4 pieces.
Put some crab mixture on each piece of muffin.
Freeze until hard.
To serve, broil for 5 minutes.

title: low fat pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in salted water as directed.
Drain well in colander.
In bowl add cooked pasta, cooked broccoli, black olives, cheese.
Pour dressing over mixture.
Let set 3 hours to marinate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain Mandarin oranges.
Drain and chop apricots and pears. Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chicken chili
directions: In a small saucepan, heat tomato juice over medium heat until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Stir well.
Microwave on High 12 to 13 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Stir in soda until foamy.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Beat with wooden spoon until mix just begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tablespoonfuls on greased waxed paper.
Stand until firm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: green bean amandine with topping
directions: Mix all ingredients well for topping.
Heat beans.
Remove from heat and add almonds.
Top individual servings with mound of sauce.
Serves 10.
Very good for holiday meals.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, and peanut butter.
Sift together baking soda and flour.
Combine creamed mixture and dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Mix with beater well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: slop pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add Sloppy Joes sauce. Make your mashed potatoes, butter and season to flavor; pour meat into pie crust (to fill).
Put the mashed potatoes over the meat and spread it evenly.
Place cheese over potatoes and bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is brown.
Let cool for 20 minutes.

title: duncan hines chocolate cake
directions: Empty cake mix into large bowl.
Add eggs, water and Crisco oil.
Mix very well with fork until smooth and thick.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, English peas, green onions and bacon.
Mix Miracle Whip and milk together and spread on top of bacon.
Add grated cheese on top.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate teddy bears
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
Chill until dough is firm enough to handle.

To shape teddy bears, for each cookie, form a portion of dough into 1 large ball for body (1 to 1 1/2-inches), 1 medium size ball for head (3/4 to 1-inch), 4 small balls for arms and legs (1/2-inch), 2 smaller balls for ears, 1 tiny ball for nose and 4 tiny balls for paws (optional).
On an ungreased cookie sheet, flatten the large ball slightly for body.
Attach medium size ball for head by overlapping slightly onto body.
Place balls for arms, legs and ears and a tiny ball on head for nose.
Arrange other tiny balls atop ends of legs for arms and paws, if desired.
With a wooden pick, draw eyes and mouth; you can also pierce a small hole at top of cookies for use as tree ornaments.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes, or until set.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store in covered container for a gift or allow cookies to dry
overnight before hanging.

title: pineapple coconut ice cream
directions: Combine half & half, cream of coconut, crushed pineapple, sugar and vanilla extract.
Stir well.
Pour into canister of ice cream freezer and add enough milk to fill canister to level shown on your freezer.
Proceed according to directions given with your brand of ice cream freezer.

title: russian taco salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Toss in a large bowl and enjoy!
Best when served right away.

title: coke cake(very moist)
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Heat butter, coke and cocoa in saucepan until mixture just bubbles around the edges.
Pour into buttermilk mixture and stir.
Add marshmallows.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool approximately 10 minutes.
Top with warm icing.

title: good candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler. Add peanut butter. Stir. Add pecans.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Add in layers the ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease pan with butter.
In a large bowl mix the bread and milk until bread is soft.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Add the sugar, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: brownies
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl until smooth. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown burger and onion; drain.
Add sauce and water; microwave on High for 8 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer sauce, raw noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers, ending in sauce.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.

title: colorful kielbasa
directions: In a large skillet, combine soup, water and margarine. Bring to boil, add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Reduce heat and simmer until rice is tender. Sprinkle with cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: gazpacho (cold soup)(serving size: 4)
directions: Put ingredients into a blender in order listed.
Cover and blend on high speed for 5 to 10 seconds or until ingredients are finely chopped.
Chill thoroughly, pour into serving bowls.

title: devil's food filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls, 2-inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookie springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature for several hours. Beat with mixer.
Add marshmallow cream and mayonnaise.
Mix on medium speed and add cherry juice.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Place in 9 x 10-inch Pyrex dish. Mix meat, garlic, barbecue sauce and spread on bottom of pan. Sprinkle onion and cheese over.
Spread mashed potatoes and cover completely.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan, blend in flour; cook over low heat until
bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and
milk to
flour mixture.
Cook over low heat until thickened,
stirring constantly.
Add
chicken,
peas
and
carrot seasonings
and eggs;
heat
well.
Spoon
into a 1 1/2 quart casserole
dish. Cover with Flaky Pastry.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: carrot cakes
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together; add flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mashed potatoes with carrots and cheese
directions: Cook potatoes until fork-tender;
drain and mash.
Cook carrots in water for 2 minutes or until tender.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add spices, egg yolks and vinegar. Beat egg whites lightly (not stiff) and add to creamed mixture. Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: peach delight
directions: Blend 1 1/2 sticks margarine with cake mix until crumbly and put in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat egg yolks and blend in sour cream and drained peaches.
Spread this mixture over cake and margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs in chili sauce
directions: Mix together chili powder,
molasses, cumin, oregano & tomato juice in electric skillet.	In a large bowl combine beef, rice, onion, green pepper, celery, egg, mustard, salt & pepper.
Blend well.
Shape into meatballs.
Place in sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover & simmer 20 minutes or until meatballs are thoroughly cooked.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and salt until tender; drain.
Put in baking dish.
Spread the cheese over the cabbage, then the chicken soup. Top with Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: frango mint dessert
directions: Line cupcake papers with wafer crumbs.

title: walnut roll
directions: Mix first seven items and separate into six balls.
Flour, then refrigerate for an hour in a greased pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into the pan; spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into an even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter or margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: broccoli-tofu-stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Stir-fry onion until tender.
Add tofu and stir-fry until lightly browned.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, ginger and vegetables.
Gently toss, coating all ingredients with sauce.
Cover and simmer over medium heat 5 minutes, until veggies are tender.
Serves 4.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain grease.
Mix in 3/4 can mushroom soup and dry onion soup with meat.
Put mixture in casserole dish; top with Tater Tots.
Dilute remaining mushroom soup until liquidy and pour over Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are warm inside and brown outside.
Can microwave for 12 to 15 minutes instead of oven.

title: soya chicken wings
directions: Wash and dry wings.
Brown ginger root in salad oil.
Mix other ingredients together, except wings.
Add slowly to oil. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add wings.
Sprinkle very lightly with salt.
Cover and simmer until done, turning often to coat wings with sauce.
Takes a little more than one hour.
Serve with fried rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 2 small bread pans. Makes flatter bread, one for now and one for later.

title: dirty rice
directions: Add water to sausage.
Fry until tender, then add butter, onions and rice.
Mix ingredients together in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet beef and noodles
directions: Brown meat and add mustard, seasoning, onion soup mix, noodles, tomatoes and water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Garnish with grated cheese or Parmesan cheese.

title: heavenly rhubarb jam
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the strawberry Jell-O until dissolved.
Pour into jars.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the milk and mix batter until smooth.

Pour the melted butter or margarine into a 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole baking dish. Pour in the batter and sprinkle blueberries on top. Bake the cobbler in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: swiss spinach quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Combine milk, eggs and seasonings. Add cheese mixture and spinach.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cherry berries
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Cover baking sheet with heavy brown paper. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue until stiff and glossy. Do not underbeat.
Spoon in 5-inch circles.
Use back of spoon to make indention.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off oven; leave in oven another hour.
Remove from oven; finish cooling away from draft.
Store in Tupperware.

title: kansas city brisket
directions: Place brisket in shallow baking pan, about the same size as the meat.
Sprinkle with liquid smoke.
Pour water in pan and bake in 350° oven, about 2 hours.
Do not cover while baking.

title: spanish rice - microwave
directions: In 2-quart microproof casserole combine all ingredients except rice.
Cook, covered, on High (max power) 5 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in rice, cook, covered, on 50 (Simmer) 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Cooking time:
35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat and potato patties
directions: Cook hamburger meat until almost done.
Add a little flour to coat all meat; set aside.
Make mashed potatoes and set aside to cool.
Lay large piece of foil down.
Put flour on one side and bread crumbs on other side.
Beat eggs.
Take and mix cold meat and potatoes; make patties.
Roll patty in flour; dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry.
Can be served with a salad.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Batter and fry chicken as normal.
Remove from frying pan. Add oil.
Add pepper and onion (slice the same so they will cook evenly).
Stir until onion and pepper are done.
Add tomatoes, hot sauce, salt, black pepper and bay leaf.
Cook on low heat until boiling.
Add chicken.
Cook until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: toffee
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and cream in a heavy saucepan.
Cook 50 minutes over low heat or until mixture forms a firm ball when a bit is dropped in ice water.
Add almonds and baking powder, stirring to mix.
Spoon into small candy cups.
Let stand until firm.
Store airtight in a cool place.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Clean and flake crabmeat.
Cream the cheese and other ingredients together.
Add crabmeat.
If desired, add finely chopped green pepper.

title: mom's super chimichangas
directions: Brown garlic and onion in oil.
Add to the mixture beef, salsa and green pepper.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: reba's lazy dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into greased cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of fruit.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's log roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in graham crackers and chopped nuts.
Place on plate in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges and eggs together.
Mix well.
(Batter will be a little thin.)
Pour into 3 greased pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: summer delight
directions: Saute squash and onion until tender.
Add sour cream, soup, salt and pepper which have been blended.
Prepare box of Stove Top stuffing and line bottom of baking dish with half the stuffing, put squash mixture on top.
Use rest of stuffing over top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave butter until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well. Microwave 5 minutes or until mixture boils.
Stir after 3 minutes. Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour in greased pan.
Let stand.

title: aunt edna's chocolate pie
directions: Brown pie shell at 425°.
Let cool.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, margarine and the yolks of the eggs.
Blend until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into pie shell.
Use the egg whites to beat into a meringue to top pie with.
Brown in a 425° oven for approximately 5 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Spread on tortillas and roll tightly.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: polish drumstick dessert
directions: Mix together; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Make tea with tea bags and 16 cups water.
Mix in juices and sugar until dissolved.
Put spices in tea ball and steep in tea mixture, long enough for spices to flavor tea.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add boiling water and cook 15 minutes in top of double boiler.
Stir often.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk. Cook until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour into pastry shell.
Top with meringue.

title: peach-pineapple jam
directions: Boil peaches, sugar and pineapple hard for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add jello (peach, orange or any fruit).
Can while hot.

title: hawaiian chicken kabobs
directions: Combine tropical salsa, honey, ginger, garlic and salt into medium bowl; mix well.
Add chicken; stir.
Let marinate at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade; reserve marinade.
Alternately thread chicken cubes, pineapple, pepper and onion squares.
Broil or grill 4 to 6 minutes or until chicken is done, turning occasionally.
Garnish skewers with cherry tomatoes. Bring marinade to a boil and brush on kabobs.
Place tropical salsa on half of plate.
Place kabob on top of the salsa.
Place over citrus wild rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ripe and rye appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine beef, cheese, olives and mayonnaise in large bowl.
Spread 1 tablespoon on each Ry-Krisp. Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in extra-large baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and egg; pour over melted margarine. Do not stir.
Add sliced peaches plus peach pie filling, vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small cobblers.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie(this pie is both delicious and pretty.)
directions: Slice strawberries and layer on top of crust.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
You can top with extra berries, if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place rice in deep casserole dish and stir in soups, water and oleo.
Place chicken on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and brown.

title: marshmallow nut fudge
directions: Lightly butter 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
In saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, evaporated milk, salt and 2 tablespoons butter to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients.
Beat vigorously until marshmallows melt.
Pour into pan.
Cool, then cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: pretzel dough
directions: Measure water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle on yeast and stir until soft.
Add salt, sugar and flour.
Mix and knead dough. Roll and twist into desired shape.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with coarse salt (optional). Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Combine all, except for Parmesan cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate chip-mint ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs and continue to beat until stiff.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into can and freeze as directed.

title: swiss beans
directions: *Melt butter; stir in flour, etc.
Cook until thick.
Fold in beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour in buttered baking dish or casserole.

title: low-fat chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken soup and onion in a pan; add 2 cans of water. Bring to a boil and cook until onions are done.
Then add 2 cups Minute rice.
Turn stove off and let set until rice is done. Serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: kraut and cabbage rolls
directions: Mix everything but cabbage and kraut.
Divide in 8 portions. Place on cabbage leaves.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.
In a Dutch oven, place 1 can of sauerkraut and place cabbage rolls. Then other can of sauerkraut.
Put water on top, up about 3/4. Bring to a boil; then cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook about 2 hours.
Serve with corn muffins.

title: play dough
directions: Boil water and oil.
Let cool.
Add salt, alum and food coloring.
Gradually add flour until stiff dough forms.
Knead in flour until good consistency.
Store at room temperature in an airtight container.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Dust with flour.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder; set aside.
In another bowl, beat egg; add sugar and zucchini and beat well.
Add oil and milk;
mix.
Stir in flour mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Add into pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes one loaf.

title: watermelon rind
directions: Soak melon rind with 4 tablespoons salt in 2 quarts water for 5 to 6 hours; drain and rinse well.
Mix cold water and ginger; cover and let set 30 minutes.
Drain and add sugar, lemon juice, 7 cups cold water and lemon slice.
Cook 30 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour in buttered baking dish.

title: cookies made with m&m's
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's and reserve the rest for decorations.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix ingredients. I use a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Delicious unfrosted cake. If frosted, use a white icing, lemon flavored.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all
ingredients, cover and chill overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until creamy. Add eggs; add buttermilk with flour and soda and vanilla. Last add chocolate mix; will be thin. Bake at 350°.

title: rose's christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in dish and freeze.
Remove from freezer an hour before serving.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook 8 minutes, no more!
Melt oleo. Add remaining ingredients.
Drain potatoes and pour in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over and bake 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: good rich punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order they are listed.
Stir and serve.
Serves 30.

title: crispix party mix
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 250° oven. Remove from oven. Stir in Season-All, lemon juice and Heinz Worcestershire sauce.
Add Crispix cereal, pretzels and nuts, stirring until well coated.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper and cool.
Makes 8 cups.

title: granny's fruit cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add 2 cups sifted flour, baking powder, spices and juice.
Add 1 cup flour in which the fruit and nuts have been mixed.
Add beaten egg whites last. Bake at 300° about 2 hours.

title: quick dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add a can of prepared pie filing. Over this, sprinkle cake mix.
Melt oleo and drizzle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.
You can use ice cream instead of Cool Whip on top.

title: easy oven fried spicy chicken
directions: Sprinkle mix over chicken.
Set aside 20 minutes.
Combine flour, salt and paprika in plastic bag.
Add few chicken pieces in bag at a time.
Shake to coat.
Dust off excess flour.
Pour oil in large baking pan.
Place chicken in single layer in pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.
Turn chicken pieces and bake until brown on both sides.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Add flour, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in greased Pyrex dish.

title: fresh fruit ambrosia
directions: Cut orange slices in quarters.
Arrange fruit in serving bowl. Combine sugar and coconut.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Add pineapple juice.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large microwave bowl, combine sugar, margarine and milk. Heat on High 9 to 11 minutes, until sugar is dissolved, stirring often. Remove and add chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla. Pour into small baking dish and cool. Cut when firm.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Cover potatoes and carrots with water or stock and cook until tender. Saute pork, onion and green pepper about 5 minutes, but do not brown. Add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook 5 minutes stirring constantly until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and serve hot.

title: summer salad
directions: Start with equal amounts of crab and shrimp; base the size of the salad you want on that.
Defrost crab and shrimp in microwave; rinse and drain.
Put into bowl with juice of 1 lemon.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Pour off liquid.
Stir.
Add your choice of the following:
shredded cheese, olives, green onions, bell pepper and celery.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to coat ingredients (enough to make them stick).
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Chill 30 minutes.
tags: Christopher Bay frozen cooked popcorn shrimp

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop large onion and saute in butter.
Add chopped broccoli, cooked and drained.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese (I use sharp Cheddar).
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.

title: german meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first 10 ingredients.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Heat oil in skillet; brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs and drain fat.
Spoon sauerkraut into skillet top with meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: budget steak
directions: Flour beef on both sides.
Fry or bake until done.
Add mushroom soup and water and simmer for 15 minutes or until desired texture.
If mushrooms are not your cup of tea, use 1 can French onion soup and 1/2 soup can of water.

title: spice island cocoa
directions: Heat 2 cups of milk, put in half and half. Mix with cocoa and spices.
Garnish with whipped cream and nutmeg.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and hot water in small mixer bowl.
Beat to spreading consistency.

title: pate
directions: Cool and serve in dish with crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter.
Roll in balls. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Melt over hot water chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip ball in chocolate, one at a time.
Put on waxed paper and place in refrigerator to harden.

title: aunt hattie lou's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar.
Add
flour, baking powder and eggs, one at a
time.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Grease tube cake pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pork chops with stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Pour off drippings.
Lightly mix the soft bread crumbs.
Add onion, melted butter, water and poultry seasoning mix.
Place a mound of stuffing on each pork chop.
Blend cream of mushroom soup with 1/3 cup water and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion until onion is transparent. Cut Velveeta into chunks and add to meat.
Add Cheez Whiz and cook over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Stir in salsa until dip is as spicy as desired.
Serve over tortilla chips or as a dip.
Makes 1 large bowl.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: In large bowl mix together flour and shortening, using pastry cutter or two forks, until mixture is crumbly.
Break egg into measuring cup, beat, then add enough cold water to measure 3/4 cup liquid.
Add baking powder and vinegar, blending well.
Then add liquid mixture to flour mixture and blend well.
Dough will be quite moist.
For best results, cover and refrigerate for at least thirty minutes before rolling out.

title: dirty rice
directions: In a skillet, brown rice and onion in butter.
Add pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1
stick
butter with crumbs.
Press into 13 x 19 x 2-inch baking
pan.
Beat
remaining butter, eggs and sugar 5 minutes. Spread
over
cracker
mixture.
Slice
bananas over this; add drained pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In a shallow dish, dip each chicken breast in milk.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes or until done.
Yields 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 10 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut first three ingredients into small pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and stir well.
Add celery seed, salt and pepper.
Chill before serving.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, then other ingredients.
Mix well with stainless spoon.
Make biscuits; place in a well-greased pan.
No need to let rise.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Keeps 2 weeks refrigerated.

title: blue cheese vegetable dip
directions: Put cheese into big mixing bowl.
Use fork to crumble cheese to desired pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and stir up with spoon.
Need to make 4 or 5 hours earlier so it can season to the right taste. Keeps for over a month.
Makes 1/2 quart.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place layer of chicken on bottom of large casserole dish.
Cover with can of soup.
Add peas and carrots.
Make batter of butter, Bisquick and buttermilk.
Pour over chicken.
Add broth.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Beat butter in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, creaming well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, lemon extract and lemon juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir thoroughly after each addition.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add 2 cups sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well blended. Form dough into 1-inch balls; roll in a mixture of the 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Place balls 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet; flatten slightly with the bottom of a drinking glass.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes or until light golden. Makes about 66.
(For holidays, add colored sugar for festive cookies.)

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Place meatballs in a 9 x 13 dish.
Blend last 4 items together.
Place on top of meatballs.
Heat at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatball sub casserole
directions: In a bowl combine onions, crumbs and parmesan cheese. Add beef and mix well. Shape into balls. Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan and bake at 400 degrees for 15 or 20 minutes. Arrange bread in a single layer in an ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, italian seasoning and pepper. Spread over bread. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese. combine sauce, water, and garlic. Add meatballs. Pour over cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: toffee
directions: Butter a square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans into pan. Heat sugar and margarine to boiling in 1-quart saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil, about 7 minutes.
Immediately spread mixture over pecans.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onions and broccoli.
Stir-fry on low heat.
Mix together cheese, eggs and cornbread mix.
Add to broccoli mixture.
Pour into medium greased pan and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and syrup, salt, vanilla and butter. Pour over pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken breast stuffed with herbed cheese
directions: Season the chicken with salt and pepper; add a little white wine.
Combine Ricotta, Parmesan, egg and herbs in small bowl. Beat until well blended.
Season with salt and pepper.
Separate skin from chicken with fingertips.
Keep skin attached around edges.
Fill the pockets generously.
Pat the skin to distribute stuffing evenly.
Tuck edges of skin under each breast.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad(makes a large size bowl)
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients, pour over veggies and chill.

title: three minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in 2-quart pan.
Heat to boiling over low heat.
Boil and stir 3 minutes or until candy thermometer registers 225°.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts, stirring until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Pour into buttered square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Will be soft.
Let set for 1 minute and remove from cookie sheet to cool.

title: joy's pot roast
directions: Sprinkle salt into bottom of a Dutch oven pot with a lid.
Heat pot on high hot enough to sizzle the roast.
Drop roast in hot pot, fattest side down first, long enough to slightly brown.
Flip roast over to brown other side.
Turn on low heat.
Sprinkle soup mix on top of roast.
Add about 1 cup of water around sides of roast. Cover pot with liquid and cook on low until roast is done.
(Takes longer for a frozen roast.)
Remove roast from pot; set aside to make gravy with drippings in the pot.

title: baked beans
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with rows of bacon.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over bacon.
Cover top of beans with bacon.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: corn cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar, eggs, oil and corn.
Mix baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt with flour.
Add both mixtures together.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slowly until mixture reaches softball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter, 1 teaspoon red food coloring and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Leave room as patties will spread out.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Layer a dish with sandwiches. Spread caramel dip on top.
Top with Cool Whip. Shake Magic Shell and spread on Cool Whip. Freeze. Cut in squares when serving. Serve frozen.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients of barbecue sauce and Italian dressing in a large bowl.
Put chicken in mixture and let set all day.
Take chicken out and bake at 350° until tender.
May also cook on grill.
You can use extra sauce if desired.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix in a medium bowl mayonnaise, buttermilk, sour cream, crumbled Bleu cheese, Accent, lemon juice, horseradish and garlic powder.
Mix well until creamy.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted boiling water for 10 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and place in casserole dish.
Add soup and milk together, pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle cheese over top of cabbage. Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheddar soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender in water. Drain. Melt butter and stir in flour; add milk and mix until smooth. Add cheese and stir until melted. Add vegetables. Thin with more milk, if necessary.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place bananas and pineapple on top.
Top with large Cool Whip. Garnish with pecans, cherries and chocolate syrup.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Roll into about 50 (1-inch) meatballs (season meat to taste). Cook thoroughly (I bake them on a broiler pan).

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream
the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs gradually and alternately with milk and flour.
Mix well.
Add flavoring and baking powder.
Cook at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Don't open oven for an hour.
Cook in tube pan.

title: best nut loaf
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, beating well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Brush top with butter.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use 3 teaspoons per cup.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish. Next, put corn flakes on top.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine, pour over the top and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: traditional party mix
directions: Melt oleo in open roasting pan in preheated 250 oven. Stir in seasoning. Gradually stir in cereals, pretzels, and nuts; stir to coat evenly. Bake 1 hour while stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool. Store in air tight container. Crispex and cheerios, 1 cup of each, can be used in place of CHEX cereal.

title: "dulan, stop by and pick up your apple pie"
directions: Slice apples thin and layer in pie crust. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over apples. Top with butter slices and then pour whipping cream over the top.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: westernized tempura
directions: Beat egg.
Add water, sugar and salt.
Combine flour and baking powder; sift into first mixture.
Fold in.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop in hot oil by spoonfuls.
Fry until golden; turn once to brown.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: Combine eggs, cinnamon and vanilla in a large shallow pan/bowl.
Add bread, turning over so it absorbs the egg.
Fry with butter or margarine until brown on all sides.
Serve with fruit jam or syrup.
Makes 4 slices.

title: bill's mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix everything together and put in 1-quart glass casserole dish.
Cover top with fine crumbs or crushed Shredded Wheat. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ground beef chow mein
directions: Cook celery, onion and ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup of water.
Add soy sauce.
Stir until thick and clear.
Add cabbage, cover and cook 10 minutes or so.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter in double boiler over hot water.
Cool slightly.
Gradually add sugar to eggs, beating after each addition.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour. Add vanilla, half the nuts and half the chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, and tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to directions; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella. Layer 1/2 noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spread with 1/2 egg and Ricotta mixture.
Add 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and milk over low heat until dissolved.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat.
Add butter once again, without stirring.
Cool.
When it has cooled entirely, add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour in buttered pan.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt ; mix well.
Put into bowl and fold in crab meat and pimentos; mix well.

title: banana pineapple loaf
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and add to butter mixture.
Fold in pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Test with toothpick for doneness.
Wonderful sliced, buttered and toasted for breakfast.
For lunch, spread cream cheese on slices and serve as a little sandwich.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Measure flour, baking soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt and sift together. Dice bananas and measure 2 cups. Add bananas to dry ingredients, along with oil, pineapple with juice, vanilla and eggs. Stir to blend mixture; do not beat. Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Set aside to cool on a rack without removing from pan.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Mix the above together and set aside.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a Bundt pan which has been sprayed with Pam and dusted with flour. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 5 to 10 minutes before removing.
Cake is very good plain; may sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: coconut island cookies
directions: Combine chocolate and coffee in small saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Set aside to cool. Combine shortening and brown sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and chocolate mixture.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in 1/3 cup coconut. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: cherry whip cream pie
directions: Whip cream, add cherries, nuts and Eagle Brand; mix together. Fold in lemon juice and pour into baked pie shells.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with mushrooms.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: mrs. homer lyon's white cake with chocolate filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Separate eggs; add the beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and the flour alternately, having sifted the baking powder with the flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake in layers in a moderate oven (350° to 375°).
Cool and ice with Chocolate
Filling.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Boil 2 minutes only. Remove from heat.
Quickly add oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls or pour into greased pan and cut into squares.
Cool.
Store as any other cookies.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add egg and molasses, mixing well. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add hot water and beat until smooth.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook meat, salt, pepper, garlic and onion until very tender. (I use pressure cooker and cook at 5 pounds pressure for 30 minutes.)
Ground meat may be used but do not pressure cook; shredded meat is better.
Use two forks to pull meat apart until shredded.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes. Mix in all other ingredients. Put in small glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbling.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits open; lay top aside.
Place bottom biscuits in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place ham over bottom of biscuits.
Put cheese over the ham.
Put top of biscuits over the cheese.
In saucepan add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until margarine melts.
Pour this over biscuits and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: elain's zucchini casserole
directions: Place butter in a heavy saucepan and melt.
Add zucchini and onion; saute over medium heat until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian vegetable supreme
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Stir-fry onion and olives in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix in vegetables and stir together.
Pour mixture into flat casserole dish.
Place sheets of Swiss cheese on top.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: homemaker's holiday
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain.
In a medium saucepan, blend soup, milk and cheese.
Cook until hot and cheese melts, stirring often. Combine macaroni, soup
mixture, luncheon meat and green pepper. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peaches-n-cream cheesecake(pie)
directions: Combine flour, butter, milk, egg, baking powder and vanilla pudding.
Pour into pan.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved juice.
Spoon over batter.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon over cream cheese filling.
Bake until brown at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp creole(serves 4)
directions: Place oil in frypan; add onions and garlic.
Cook slowly until tender, but not brown.
Add flour, stirring until brown.
Add raw shrimp; saute until they turn pink.
