Watch closely and stir.
Add parsley; cook a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and Tabasco and Worcestershire sauces.
Add mushroom soup and cook about 20 minutes, or until shrimp is done.
Serve over rice.

title: stuff-it
directions: Saute green onions, white onion and celery in butter.
Add crabmeat, stirring constantly.
Add bread crumbs, paprika, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Stir.
Add shrimp and beaten egg.
The egg holds the mixture together.
If too loose, add more bread crumbs.
Never cover the mixture.
This can be served in individual ramekins garnished with a lemon wedge or as an entree used as stuffing for shrimp or fish.
Freeze in patties and thaw as needed.

title: grilled zucchini parmesan
directions: Squeeze excess moisture from squash.
Place on heavy-duty foil.
Dot with butter and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Seal foil and grill over medium-hot coals 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: easy cheese batter bread
directions: Melt butter in milk and water.
In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and rest of ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir remaining flour.
Cover.
Let rise until light (45 to 60 minutes; dough does not double).
Generously grease bottom and sides of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Stir down dough. Place in greased pan.

title: cool pudding mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with favorite fruits (drained canned mandarin oranges, banana slices dipped in lemon juice and pineapple chunks topped with pecans, if desired).
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, let cool and shred in large skillet. Cook spanish rice and add to skillet along with refried
beans, taco seasoning, salsa, and half of one can of enchilada sauce.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to brown sugar mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Remove from pan when cool. Makes about 36 bars.

title: fideo
directions: Brown vermicelli in oil.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Cover and cook on low heat until tender, about 15 minutes.
Good served with tacos.
Top with picante sauce for added flavor.

title: beans
directions: Drain all but 1 can of beans.
Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Brown bacon.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until hot.

title: ham n' cheese bake(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender-crisp.
Add green peppers, celery, rice, broth, salt, curry powder and ham.
Stir well, cover, and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is gone.
Remove from oven.
Add pineapple chunks and cheese.
Toss lightly.

title: crazy cheese cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as it is on the box.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put cake mixture in pan but do not bake.
Mix sugar, eggs, Ricotta and vanilla.
Spread mixture on top of cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat till cheese melts

title: atre johnson's steak
directions: Flatten steak thin; add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute onions and parsley in butter; add tomato juice.
Add sauce to rice.
Spoon rice mixture on meat; roll and tie.
Brown roll on top of stove in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: microwave cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box, substituting juice for water.
Fold pineapple into cake batter.
Pour batter into microwave-safe baking dish.
Cook on High power for 13 minutes.
Let stand in dish for 5 minutes more.
Then turn out on cake plate.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli per package directions.
Saute onion and celery in small amount of margarine.
Combine all ingredients and stir cheese and soup until well blended.
Spoon in a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10. Freezes well.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until done. Drain off excess grease. Add all tomato products and spices. Cook on medium heat until bubbly. Turn heat down on low and let simmer 2 to 3 hours. Add mushrooms and simmer for at least 1 to 2 more hours. This is an all-day sauce.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Using electric mixer, cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice. Stir into pumpkin mixture. Stir in chopped walnuts and raisins. Drop by tablespoon onto well-greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until golden on edges. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Gently toss together all ingredients. Cover and chill several hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli by package directions.
Add melted Cheez Whiz, rice and soup.
Mix well and serve.

title: vegetable special
directions: Fry onions and peppers in oil.
Add corn and tomatoes. Stir and heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: biscuit supreme
directions: Sift flour; combine with baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Stir until mixture clumps together. Knead gently on a floured surface for 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Transfer to ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops of biscuits with milk.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: old suzanna pie
directions: In a skillet over low heat, mix coconut, nuts and butter together, stirring well, until coconut is lightly toasted; set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, milk and cream cheese in mixer bowl until smooth.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip mixture in pie crust. Drizzle with caramel, then spread a layer of coconut mixture. Repeat with a second layer, ending with coconut mixture.
Place in a 1-gallon freezer bag and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: tamale dip
directions: Heat chili and cheeses.
Add chopped tamales.
Pour into dish.
Add shredded cheese, ripe olives and green onions to top.

title: texas avocado tea sandwiches
directions: Mash avocado; add lemon juice. Stir in almonds and bacon. Add seasonings. Mix to creamy smoothness and spread between slices of tea sandwich bread.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Heat peanut butter, sugar and syrup on stove or in microwave until dissolved.
Add cereal.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 package chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coffee-time gems
directions: In mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and brown sugar.
Combine egg, sour cream, milk, melted margarine and coffee granules.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to dry ingredients.
Fold in chopped dates.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flavorings.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg, then add flour and baking powder.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Cover with thick slices of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and lemon juice.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy corn
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter, milk and onion salt in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often, until cheese melts. Stir in corn; cook, stirring constantly, until thoroughly
heated. Yields 8 servings.

title: hard times cake
directions: Bake in layers and spread with cooked sweetened apples.

title: vinegar taffy
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and vinegar.
Stir well over medium-high heat.
Boil until tests brittle in cool water (spins a long thread from spoon).
Butter hands and pour taffy onto buttered plate to cool.
Taffy must be pulled by hand and twisted. Pull into size of pencil in long ropes.
Taffy will be white.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut off crusts from the bread.
Butter bread; line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with bread, buttered side down.
Layer with ham, onion and cheese.
Mix milk and beaten eggs.
Pour over layers. Break bread crusts into squares and layer over egg mixture.
Pour butter over bread crumbs; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add rice and stir until it is browned evenly.
Pour in baking dish and add soup and consomme.
Cover and bake at 350° until rice is tender, at least 45 minutes.

title: susan's thick and juicy blueberry sauce
directions: Simmer fruit and water for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Stir this dry mixture into the simmered fruit. Cook for a few minutes until thickened.
Serve over ice cream (shortcake, angel food cake, etc.), warm or chilled.

title: breakfast pinwheels(oatmeal bread)
directions: Add shortening, sugar, molasses and salt.
Then yeast that has
been dissolved in warm water. Gradually add flour until a soft dough forms - knead on a floured board - let rise one hour. Punch down and shape into loaves.
Let rise double in bulk.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: ratatouille
directions: Repeat layers.
Drizzle over top 1/2 cup olive oil.
Pour in 2 small cans tomato sauce.
Bake covered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Soup with leftover.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Add 1/3 mixture to salad ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce and top with remaining dressing.
Serve immediately upon removal from refrigerator.

title: yummies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; mix well.
Add chopped dates and coconut.
Cook over medium heat for about 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well.
Let cool.
Shape into balls; roll in powdered sugar.

title: harriett's strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries; drain.
I pat them dry with paper towels. Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thickened.
Remove from stove.
Add strawberry jello and red cake coloring.
Pour over strawberries; mix well.
Pour into the baked pie shell. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend well, sugar, eggs, oil, salt, cinnamon, water and pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Put into muffin tins, lightly greased and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 30 muffins.

title: original chex party mix
directions: Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt; mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into a large plastic bag. Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside plastic bag. Seal bag securely.
Shake well.
Pour contents of bag into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring thoroughly every 2 minutes.
While stirring, make sure to scrape sides and bottom of bowl.
Spread on absorbent towel to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: california quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg with a wire whisk; blend in flour and beat in mayonnaise.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in cheese, crab and onion.
Fill pie shell and bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mrs. fields' cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and oatmeal together, put in blender a little at a time.
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda to flour.
Mix all together.
Add chocolate chips, chocolate bar and nuts.
Make golf ball size mounds.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Stir cake mix, egg and Cool Whip together by hand until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar.
Roll around, form into ball and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light golden (not brown).
Immediately use spatula to take up and cool on wire racks.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook
broccoli
as package directs.
Arrange chicken in baking dish;
top with broccoli and butter.
Then combine soup and cheese,
heat.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli. Brown lightly under broiler.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix eggs, 10x sugar and cream cheese together and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift again. Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in crushed pineapple; add flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 medium size muffins.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Boil peaches, margarine and vanilla about 1 minute. Pour in 9 x 13 pan. Mix flour, milk and sugar. Pour on top of peaches and bake at 350° until done.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Scatter meat on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle corn over meat, cover with slices of Velveeta. Add chopped onion and cover with crushed Doritos.

title: scroodle noodle
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and salts.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese and cooked noodles. Place cheese on top and heat at 350° until melted.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, to make a soft dough. Form into 2 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator or freezer.
When ready to bake, remove from freezer; thaw 10 minutes.
Cut into thin slices; place on ungreased cookie sheet. Top each with a pecan half.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove to rack to cool.

title: 1917 war cake
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in saucepan; cook for 3 minutes. After mixture reaches boiling point, add Crisco when cool.
Add soda, dissolved in a little hot water.
Add flour and baking powder; stir.
Pour into tube pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: rogan gosht(lamb curry)
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add all other ingredients except saffron and hot water.
Cook for 25 minutes, or until meat is browned.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Dissolve saffron in 1 tablespoon hot water and add just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut butter into dry ingredients (not very fine).
Pour milk in and stir until moistened.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Spoon out 6 scones per cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: corey's chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased baking dish with asparagus.
Mix other ingredients and pour over asparagus.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar and baking powder. Add butter and blend with pastry blender. Sprinkle 1/2 of crumbs in square pan. Cook apples, sugar and cinnamon together until sugar is dissolved. Spread on crumbs in pan. Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Place tomato slices on a baking sheet and drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with garlic, oregano, basil and onions.
Top with cheese. Sprinkle bacon bits over top and place under broiler for 10 minutes or until bubbly and slightly brown.
Serve hot.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine all ingredients except tomatoes in small bowl and blend well.
Gently spread mixture about 1/4-inch thick on tomatoes.
Broil 4 inches from heat source 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned, watching carefully so that the topping does not burn.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable square(can be very creative!)
directions: Spread Pillsbury
crescent
rolls
on
cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese and Hidden Valley
Ranch powder. Spread on crescent rolls. Top with chopped
vegetables,
then	add shredded cheese and bacon bits. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: bubbly punch
directions: In a large pitcher, mix together one 24 ounce can unsweetened frozen apple juice concentrate, 2 (24 ounce) cans cold water and one (32 ounce) bottle club soda.
Stir well and pour into plastic glasses.
Makes 17 small servings.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add flour and sugars.
Stir together, then add water and butter.
Blend well.
Add milk and cook until thick. Add vanilla.
Stir and cool.
Add sliced bananas and top with chopped salted nuts before serving.
(Warming the milk before adding cuts down on cooking time; this also works well to cook in the microwave.)

title: imperial crab
directions: Beat egg and combine all ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vinegar and salt.
Heat to dissolve sugar. Stir in all beans, onion and pepper.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Blend in shortening with knife or dough wire blender.
Mix egg and milk.
Add slowly to dry mixture by placing egg and milk mixture at the edge of bowl, mixing together a little at a time.
Knead lightly.
Roll out on floured board or counter to desired thickness and cut with floured cutter.
Bake in hot 450° oven about 15 minutes.

title: best ever plain peas
directions: Sort and wash peas.
Place in large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above peas.
Let soak for 8 hours; drain.
Add 6 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 cups.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover for first half of baking time.
After taking out of oven, you can add more grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.

title: minie's morsels for mature cats
directions: Pour contents of sardine can into medium bowl.
Using fork, mash sardines.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop 1/4 teaspoonful of mixture at a time on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 7 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: chess bars
directions: Combine butter, 1 egg and cake mix in bowl.
Mix well.
Press over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 eggs, confectioners sugar and cream cheese in bowl.
Pour over cake mix layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: crowd pleaser trail mix
directions: Mix together in any amount desired and store in a large airtight container.
This goes fast with kids and adults!

title: scalloped potatoes on the grill
directions: Wrap potatoes, topped with seasonings, in tinfoil. Cook on grill until tender (about 1 hour).
Open foil; top potatoes with cheese slices.
Cover back up and cook until cheese melts (about 15 to 20 minutes).
This can also be cooked in the oven at 350° using same procedure.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix in all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake very slow.
Keep pan of water below cake while baking.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Soak chicken in soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce mixture, about 15 minutes.
Roll chicken around cheese slice.
Wrap 1/2 bacon slice around chicken.
Poke toothpicks through to hold together and bake, broil or best to grill.

title: salad
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain off juice.
Mix with dressing and let stand for 1 hour until ready to eat.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk, mix until thickened.
Mix in Cool Whip.
In a 9 X 13 pan, layer crackers and mixture beginning with crackers and ending with crackers.

title: spaghetti or tomato sauce
directions: In saucepan, heat olive oil and lightly brown onion and garlic.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, black pepper and salt.
Simmer gently about 10 minutes.
Stir well until tomato paste is dissolved.

title: beef burgundy stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pan, heat the oil; add the bacon and saute until golden brown.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Season the 3 pounds of beef with 1 tablespoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Saute the beef, onions and carrots until golden brown.
Drain off the fat and add the shallots, garlic and the flour.
Mix well and allow to stand in the oven for a few minutes until the flour becomes golden brown.
Remove pan from oven and add the burgundy and the beef stock.
Be sure that the meat is covered by the liquid.
Add the parsley, celery pieces, the bay leaf and the thyme to the pot; bring to a boil and then cook over low heat for 2 hours or until meat is well done.
If the sauce is too thick, you may add a little stock to thin it out.
While all this is going on, saute the mushrooms in the butter on high heat for 3 minutes, then add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook for 2 more minutes and add to beef.
When the beef is ready, remove the bay leaf and the 4 pieces of celery before serving.
Serve with boiled potatoes or noodles.

title: happy day cake(great for shortcake)
directions: Mix butter and eggs together.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and baking powder.
Blend.
Add the milk and flour alternately.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: paul newman's wanna-be spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain grease.
Mix meats and all ingredients together.
Simmer on low heat for 1 to 2 hours. May freeze leftovers or works well with lasagne.

title: microwave pecan pie
directions: Put pastry shell in glass pie plate.
Place butter in medium glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on Roast for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except baked pastry shell.
Mix well.
Pour filling in shell.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown onion and meat in skillet.
Mix rice, juice, salt and pepper; sugar to taste. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breast divan
directions: Partially boil chicken breasts for 1/2 hour.
When cool remove skin and bones.
Cook broccoli until almost done, about 5 minutes. Do not overcook.
Heat soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice over medium heat.
In a long baking dish or pan, cover bottom with cooked broccoli in a single layer.
Arrange chicken breasts in a single layer over broccoli.
Pour sauce mixture over top. Sprinkle with grated cheese over the entire top.
Use a generous amount for a bubbly, cheesy taste.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Do not cover.
Can be prepared the day before.
Cover and refrigerate.
Uncover before baking.

title: homemade cranberry sauce(yields 2 cups)
directions: Combine sugar and water in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish. Add cranberries.
Cover with plastic and vent one side.

After 4 minutes, until they are soft and have started to pop open, 8 to 10 minutes, remove the plastic wrap and continue cooking on High, stirring after 5 minutes, until mixture has thickened, about 10 minutes.
Let sauce stand until it has cooled to room temperature. Add grated orange, lemon or chopped nutmeats if desired.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook onion and pepper until transparent in the oil.
Add meat and cook until it is browned.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and let simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir in soup and pour in casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Drain and chill fruit.
Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add 1 cup fruit juice.
Stir in apricots and pineapple.
Add marshmallows. Chill until firm.
Spread with topping.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix lime jello, boiling water and lemon juice together; add to cheese mixture.
Chill and when starts to set, beat mixture and add vanilla and Dream Whip. Can be frozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order that they are listed. Bake in a 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add chocolate.
Alternately add flour, salt and soda with buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend and scrape bowl.
Slowly pour water over batter and blend again.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 or so minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Sprinkle with broken pecans (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dill slices
directions: Slice pickles into circles.
Blend with other ingredients; return to jar.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large, heavy pot, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add the onions and cook over high heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then reduce heat to medium.
Add the sugar and cook until onions are golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: campfire scramble
directions: In a heavy 10-inch skillet, arrange bacon slices.
Cook until bacon is crisp.
Remove and crumble bacon.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add potatoes to skillet.
Sprinkle with a dash of salt and pepper.
Return to stove and stir-fry until potatoes are light brown.
Beat eggs, milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook without stirring until mixture begins to settle on bottom and around edges; stir.
Cook about 4 minutes.
Arrange crumbled bacon on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Rinse.
Add fresh water and cook with pepper and quartered onion for 2 hours.
Slice celery in small pieces.
Cut bacon and sausage in 1-inch pieces.
Add along with celery and tomatoes to beans and cook covered on low for 30 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 4.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
In a greased baking dish, put a layer of rice, a layer of cheese, half of soup, remainder of rice, cheese and soup.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: mixed vegetables with pasta
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in chicken broth.
Add tomatoes and basil.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add vegetables and cook 10 minutes or until tender but crisp.
Stir often.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 2 large servings.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Top with pastry.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Smash bananas; beat in eggs.
Sift in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blintz kuchen
directions: Grease bottom of an 8-inch round cake pan.

title: jewish cookie bars
directions: Cream 3/4 cup margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and 3 tablespoons cocoa; mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir all together in a 2 1/2-quart ovensafe bowl. (Bowl should only be 3/4 full, so that potatoes don't boil over while baking.) Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Will be brown on top.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and orange pieces well.
Add cottage cheese and stir in.
Pour dry jello powder over mixture; stir well.
Add the Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all together and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve with crackers.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Combine mayonnaise, curry powder, onion, prepared mustard, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce in bowl; mix well.
Chill, tightly covered, for 2 hours.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla, orange rind and egg. Mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until well blended. Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar immediately after removing from oven.

title: easy no fail pie dough
directions: Mix well, divide in half.
Roll out or you can pat this in pie dish by hand.

title: scalloped potatoes and onions
directions: In casserole, layer potatoes and onion.
In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine and stir in flour; cook until foamy. Gradually stir in broth and mayo.
Cook until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Season and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are fork-tender and top is brown.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs and sorghum.
Put dry ingredients in a bowl and mix with a wire whip to blend, then add to the other ingredients.
Chill.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve.
Add a few maraschino cherries (chopped) for color.

title: microwave rice krispies treats
directions: Butter 9 x 9 pan (or 9 X 13).
In large glass mixing bowl; microwave margarine and marshmallows for 2 minutes, full power. Stir to combine.
Microwave for another 1 1/2-2 minutes, full power.
Stir until smooth; add cereal.
Stir until well coated. Press into pan using buttered spatula and waxed paper.
Cut into squares when cool, or partially cool.
9 X 13 pan makes 24 (2 X 2) squares.
Note:
May also add M&M's and nuts with cereal.
Total cooking time: 5-10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt shortening and stir until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Stir in flour and mix until all is well blended.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead well, about 5 minutes.
Place in a a greased pan, covered with a cloth, for 1 hour over a pan of warm (not hot) water and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead down again.
Place over warm water again for about 30 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch thick on a slightly greased surface.
Spread with 2 tablespoons softened margarine, sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon mixed together.
Roll up and cut into desired thickness.
Place in a greased pan with brown sugar in the bottom. Let rise for about 45 minutes and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, mushrooms, onion and Swiss cheese together.
Mix the dressing:
Hellmann's, sugar and vinegar. Pour over salad just before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Put in undrained pineapple, swirling it around to fill corners.
Spoon in pie filling evenly. Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the fruit to cover it all.
Melt butter and dribble over top or distribute bits over the top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° until browned (about 1 hour). Serve with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.

title: pastor larry's hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 30 minutes, then put into hot jars and seal.

title: turkey marsala
directions: Lightly sprinkle spices on meat.
In a bowl, mix flour and cheese. Dip meat into flour and cheese mixture. Shake excess off. In a large skillet or pan, melt butter and olive oil.
Lightly sprinkle pan with garlic salt. Keep on medium heat. Fry meat for 30 seconds on each side. To create sauce, mix wine and lemon juice.
Pour over meat.
Simmer for about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put on a plate and pour remaining juices onto meat. Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Combine ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
Layer noodles, meat and sauce and cheeses 3 times with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water, eggs and food coloring.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with a cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
tags: Duncan Hines cherry supreme cake mix

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Place both packages of broccoli in microwave on High 5 minutes.
Drain broccoli well and arrange in an 8 x 12-inch dish, alternating heads and stems.
Top with ham, half of onion rings and cheese.
Blend soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings on top. Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until casserole is heated through.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer macaroni and Cheddar cheese alternately in 2-quart baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Combine tomato and seasonings in bowl, mixing well.
Pour tomato mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Bake, covered at 400° for 45 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings, about 430 calories each.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and drain grease off.
Melt Velveeta in crock-pot; add other ingredients and mix.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry pudding mix with pineapple with its own juice.
Blend in marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill for a few hours before serving.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Heat until dissolved (don't boil).
The recipe can be doubled.
If thicker syrup is desired, add sugar or delete water.

title: baked chicken and rice(excellent for dinner party)
directions: Prepare rice ahead of time.
Place cooked rice on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle half of the soup mix over rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle remaining soup mix over chicken.
Pour evaporated milk over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot ham and cheese buns
directions: Cut sliced ham and sharp cheese into 1/4-inch cubes. Combine with onions, hard-boiled eggs and sliced peppers (or stuffed olives). Mix salad dressing and chili sauce and add to ham and cheese mixture. Mix well and spread on hot dog buns. Wrap each in foil. Twist ends securely. Bake for 10 minutes in 400° oven or until buns are hot.

title: blueberry, maple and walnut quick bread
directions: Combine and beat eggs, sugar, sour cream, syrup and vanilla. Stir in bran flakes.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking soda. Add 1 cup blueberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: three day cake
directions: Make 2 layer cake. Split layers in half with thread. Turn cake over so it can soak in cake. Mix up sour cream and 2 cups sugar. Set 1 cup of the mixture aside. With the rest, add coconut and pineapple. Mix together; spread mixture between each layer.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches of oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Combine cornmeal, sugar and soda.
Beat 1 1/4 cups buttermilk, egg and shortening together with a fork.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients until thoroughly blended.

title: grandma's grape-nut pudding(easy)
directions: Butter glass dish.
Add ingredients.
Just stir well.
Let set at least 1/2 hour.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry strawberry jam
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Chop cherries; measure and add enough reserved juice to make 2 cups.
Combine fruits, sugar and lemon juice in a large saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin at once.
Skim off foam for 5 minutes.
Quickly pour into hot scalded jars and seal.
Makes six 1/2-pint jars.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to box directions.
Whip in Cool Whip.
Layer the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Add 1/2 of the pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Layer with graham crackers.
Repeat.
Top with icing.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: many bean baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake for 3 hours at 325°, uncovered.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Arrange asparagus spears, broccoli flowerets, snow peas, yellow squash and zucchini in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Set aside.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray, place over medium high heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and garlic, saute 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Add reserved vegetables, chives and 1 tablespoon water; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Set vegetable mixture aside.
Cook linguine according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken strips in bottom layer of casserole dish.
Pour over cream of chicken soup; lay cheese on top.
Mix dressing mix as directed on package; put on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until chicken is done.

title: walnut fried shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Rinse well and set aside.
Combine flour, pepper and salt; stir well.
Combine milk and eggs; stir well.
Dip shrimp in egg mixture; dredge in flour mixture.
Dip shrimp in egg mixture again and dredge in ground walnuts.
Place coated shrimp on a wax paper lined baking sheet; cover and freeze 2 hours.
Fry shrimp, a few at a time, in deep hot oil (350°) 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 3.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cut ham, bell pepper and onion into small pieces.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Shape into ball.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar (to make it easier to mix, I melt the oleo, but then be sure to chill dough several hours).
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll lightly in sugar; do not flatten.
Bake at 375°, 3 inches apart on ungreased tin.

title: cheese twists
directions: Cut pastry in half (cut straight through dough).
Refrigerate 1/2 of dough.
Roll out to 8 x 10-inch rectangle.
Mix egg and mustard and spread over dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese; press lightly.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of pepper.
Cut crosswise into 12 strips.
Twist each strip about 3 times.
Arrange on baking sheet (nonstick) and chill 30 minutes.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 5 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Brown in oil over high heat; add onions.
Saute until tender.
Blend soup in water, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak.
Add mushrooms. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt the chips and peanut butter and pour half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill firm.
Keep other half warm.

title: vegetable salad(spinach)
directions: Blend together and pour over peas.
Add 1/2 cup grated Swiss cheese on top.
Cover and chill 12 hours.
Do not toss.
Serve.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt oleo and cheese.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa.
Mix ingredients and add vanilla and nuts.
Put in greased 9 x 13; cut into small pieces and serve.

title: chili
directions: Mix beef with small amount of water.
Brown ground beef with a sprinkling of salt.
Add spices after meat turns and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Add catsup, bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pecan cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour with enough milk to mix.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add syrup, salt, remainder of milk, margarine and pecans.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add vanilla; pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until forms a peak.
Place on filling.
Bake until brown.

title: cherry-cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Turn cherries into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Meanwhile, with electric mixer, beat cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and then sour cream. Carefully, spoon mixture over cherries and bake 30 minutes more. When done, sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Cool cake.
Prepare pudding per directions.
In a large bowl, layer 1/2 chocolate pudding. Then layer 1/2 of baked cake, broken into pieces, then more pudding.
Pour 1/2 of Kahlua over cake.
Spoon 1/2 of Cool Whip onto cake and top with candy bars.
You should have enough ingredients for 2 complete layers.

title: french fried ice cream
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Take a scoop of ice cream and roll it in crumbs.
Pack crumbs firmly with hands.
Dip in egg-milk mixture, then roll again in crumbs; pack firmly.
Wrap in plastic wrap or aluminum foil and freeze.

title: lazy day overnight lasagna
directions: In a saucepan, put in ground beef, spaghetti sauce and water. Let simmer for at least 10 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add milk; mix well.
Strain into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes; reduce oven to 350° until center of custard is firm and knife inserted comes out clean.

title: rocky road s'mores bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: diabetic salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Shape in loaf and place in baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Take out half of the soft dough.
Add soda and baking powder.
Mix in well.
Place on floured board and add enough flour to make the dough stiff enough to roll out and cut.
Bake biscuits until lightly brown.
Add more flour and warm water to the leftover dough.
In about 5 hours, it will be ready to make biscuits.
Can be kept going for as long as you need it.

title: classic beef barbecue(great!!  serves 10 to 12.)
directions: Put meat in Dutch oven and top with onion and celery.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil water.
Pour over Jell-O.
Dissolve good.
When cool, stir in all vegetables, mayonnaise and cheese.
Put pecans in last.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate.
I add one envelope of Knox gelatine to be sure it is firm.
Good to serve at any meal.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in baking dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Shake to mix.
Add chicken; shake to coat.
Remove chicken; reserve flour. In large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon of oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown on one side about 5 minutes.
Add remaining oil, turn and brown chicken well on second side.
Transfer chicken to plate; set aside.
Add margarine to skillet; when melted, add onion and cook until softened.
Stir in reserved flour.
Cook, stirring, until flour is completely incorporated.
Add broth, 2 tablespoons of lemon juice and thyme; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover.
Cook until chicken is tender and opaque (5 minutes).
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Stir in 1 tablespoon lemon juice in skillet and pour over chicken.
Serve chicken with lemon wedge, sprinkling parsley if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: penny supper
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy scalloped tuna and potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring until smooth.
Take off heat and add 1/2 cup of cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange tuna and potatoes in layers in buttered casserole (3-quart size).
Pour sauce over all and top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.
Easy dish for company.

title: hot chicken salad deluxe
directions: Brown almonds in oven.
Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add soup, milk, Doritos and chilies.
Mix well.
Lay cheese on top.
Heat in a 300° oven.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Empty milk into large bowl and stir in lemon juice and instant pudding.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Put into graham cracker crust and chill.
Refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thick. Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of baking dish.
Add layer of bananas and cream or keep alternating layers, finishing with pudding mixture.

title: praline cheese cake
directions: Combine and press in a 9-inch spring pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: date and cheese bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let stand 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add date mixture, eggs, cheese and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in waxpaper lined loaf pan in moderate oven about 50 minutes.
